06:46.022 --> 06:48.013
Don't take it off yet.

07:04.307 --> 07:05.604
Looks white, don't it?

07:05.808 --> 07:06.866
All right!

07:07.543 --> 07:09.272
Well, all root!

07:09.479 --> 07:10.503
All reet!

07:29.232 --> 07:31.223
Hit the brim with the left.

07:50.753 --> 07:53.153
<i>When my mother was pregnant with me...</i>

07:54.090 --> 07:58.186
<i>...a party of Klansmen surrounded</i>
<i>our house in Omaha, Nebraska.</i>

07:58.394 --> 08:02.091
<i>They brandished guns and shouted</i>
<i>for my father to come out.</i>

08:04.800 --> 08:07.564
<i>My pregnant mother went to the door...</i>

08:07.770 --> 08:10.762
<i>...and said that my father was in</i>
<i>Milwaukee, preaching.</i>

08:11.274 --> 08:13.640
<i>They said that good white Christians...</i>

08:13.843 --> 08:17.472
<i>...would not stand for his</i>
<i>troublemaking and to get out of town.</i>

08:36.097 --> 08:39.499
<i>They broke every window with</i>
<i>their rifles before riding away.</i>

08:41.370 --> 08:45.397
<i>They rode off into the moonlight as</i>
<i>suddenly as they had come.</i>

08:46.909 --> 08:51.369
<i>My father was not a frightened Negro,</i>
<i>as most were and many still are today.</i>

08:51.581 --> 08:53.879
<i>He was 6 feet 4 and very strong.</i>

08:54.083 --> 08:55.948
<i>He believed, as did Marcus Garvey...</i>

08:56.152 --> 08:58.552
<i>...that freedom, independence</i>
<i>and self-respect...</i>

08:58.754 --> 09:00.449
<i>...wouldn't be achieved</i>
<i>by Negroes in America.</i>

09:00.656 --> 09:05.593
--The object of building up for
themselves a great nation in Africa.

09:06.095 --> 09:07.119
<i>Therefore...</i>

09:07.330 --> 09:10.993
<i>...black men should leave America and</i>
<i>return to their land of origin.</i>

09:12.935 --> 09:15.563
<i>My father dedicated his life</i>
<i>to his beliefs...</i>

09:15.771 --> 09:18.535
<i>...because four of his six brothers</i>
<i>died violently.</i>

09:18.741 --> 09:21.676
<i>Three killed by white men,</i>
<i>and one lynched.</i>

09:21.944 --> 09:24.174
<i>There were nine children in our family.</i>

09:24.780 --> 09:28.341
<i>My mother was a proud woman, an</i>
<i>educated woman, a strong woman.</i>

09:29.452 --> 09:33.479
<i>She was fair-skinned because her mother</i>
<i>was raped by a white man.</i>

09:33.689 --> 09:37.352
<i>One reason she married my father was</i>
<i>because he was so black.</i>

09:37.727 --> 09:41.993
<i>She hated her complexion and wanted</i>
<i>her children to have some color.</i>

09:42.698 --> 09:47.362
<i>I think this had a profound effect on</i>
<i>me then and on most Negroes today.</i>

09:48.004 --> 09:52.668
<i>Because so many of our sisters have been</i>
<i>raped or violated by the white man...</i>

09:52.875 --> 09:56.777
<i>...black men can't wait to get their</i>
<i>hands on the white man's prize:</i>

09:56.979 --> 09:58.640
<i>A white woman.</i>

10:01.050 --> 10:03.644
Africa for the Africans!

10:05.388 --> 10:06.878
Say "Roseland."

10:08.591 --> 10:11.287
Showtime!

10:11.827 --> 10:14.057
Showtime!

10:43.559 --> 10:44.753
Hi, Shorty!

10:46.329 --> 10:47.421
You're too big!

10:47.630 --> 10:48.927
I'm gonna come get you.

10:55.237 --> 10:58.263
Come on, Shorty,
I've gotta dance!

11:08.584 --> 11:10.745
You in charge, boy!

11:13.622 --> 11:15.453
You like what you see, baby?

11:18.527 --> 11:19.357
Get back here!

11:19.562 --> 11:20.654
Go ahead, boy!

11:20.863 --> 11:22.558
Red, save me! Save me!

11:22.765 --> 11:23.595
Gotcha!

11:35.044 --> 11:37.979
Come on, Shorty. I wanna dance again!

13:42.271 --> 13:44.398
Laura sure can go, can't she?

13:44.607 --> 13:46.632
-I gotta go freshen up.
-All right.

13:46.842 --> 13:49.174
-You come on back now.
-All right, Malcolm.

13:49.979 --> 13:52.607
That chick is fine as May wine.

13:52.882 --> 13:56.249
Except she lives up on a hill
and got a grandmother too.

13:56.452 --> 13:59.615
She a church girl.
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

14:20.943 --> 14:22.535
Wanna dance?

14:48.604 --> 14:50.037
So what do they call you?

14:51.173 --> 14:52.162
Red.

14:55.945 --> 14:56.877
I'm Sophia.

14:57.513 --> 14:58.571
How you doing?

14:58.781 --> 15:00.612
Very well, thank you.

15:01.350 --> 15:02.977
I have an idea, Red.

15:05.354 --> 15:08.881
Why don't you take that
little girl home and come on back?

15:16.732 --> 15:18.859
Just walk, baby, don't run.

15:20.736 --> 15:22.670
It'll be here when you get back.

15:38.220 --> 15:40.188
Well, I better not come in.

15:40.389 --> 15:41.981
I'm not stupid.

15:43.058 --> 15:44.047
It's late, baby.

15:44.259 --> 15:47.285
I know where you're going.
I am not a total square.

15:47.496 --> 15:50.863
-I know what's happening--
-I gotta go home. It's late.

15:51.066 --> 15:54.900
I gotta get up early in the morning.
I gotta work tomorrow.

15:57.773 --> 15:59.240
I'll call you tomorrow?

15:59.441 --> 16:00.999
What for?

16:01.276 --> 16:05.906
I'm not white and I don't put out,
so why would you want to call me?

16:10.119 --> 16:12.849
Good night, Mrs. Johnson.
I'll call you tomorrow.

17:06.474 --> 17:08.965
Am I the first white woman
you've been with?

17:11.079 --> 17:12.411
No, you ain't.

17:12.748 --> 17:14.909
Shit, I done had plenty.

17:16.852 --> 17:18.410
That isn't a whore?

17:36.505 --> 17:37.529
Take your time.

17:37.740 --> 17:41.267
Sophia's not going anywhere.

17:42.411 --> 17:43.844
I told you to walk...

17:44.346 --> 17:45.779
...don't run.

17:48.851 --> 17:51.012
I don't like women that talk too much.

17:55.524 --> 17:57.082
Who wants to talk?

18:16.145 --> 18:17.840
You missed me.

18:18.046 --> 18:19.980
Try this on for size.

18:24.086 --> 18:25.713
-I ducked.
-You ducked?

18:25.921 --> 18:28.185
You didn't! I got you
right between the toes!

18:28.390 --> 18:31.848
I'm tired of playing the cops.
I wanna be Bogart.

18:32.060 --> 18:34.927
Shorty, you're too small to be Bogart.

18:35.130 --> 18:36.791
I'm not too short to be Cagney.

18:40.769 --> 18:42.236
One more!

18:46.708 --> 18:50.235
You dirty, rotten, stinking copper!

18:56.618 --> 18:58.085
You used to be a big shot.

19:03.091 --> 19:05.218
There is just nothing I can do.

19:05.427 --> 19:08.658
-What do you mean, took his own life?
-You heard the verdict.

19:08.864 --> 19:13.665
Verdict? A man takes a hammer and
bashes in the back of his own head?

19:13.869 --> 19:16.235
Then he lays on the tracks
and kills himself?

19:16.772 --> 19:19.070
We only act on the verdicts,
we don't make them.

19:19.274 --> 19:21.174
Do you pay or don't you?

19:26.281 --> 19:27.680
Read the policy, ma'am.

19:28.517 --> 19:31.042
It clearly states....

19:39.461 --> 19:40.485
Come here, Sophia.

19:50.539 --> 19:52.131
You're the man.

19:54.176 --> 19:55.575
Sit down.

20:01.750 --> 20:03.377
What's your story?

20:03.585 --> 20:06.816
You one of them white chicks
can't get enough colored studs?

20:17.566 --> 20:19.227
IKiss my foot.

20:21.770 --> 20:23.601
Go ahead, kiss it.

20:32.848 --> 20:34.475
Now feed me.

20:55.304 --> 20:57.135
That's your story, girl.

20:58.006 --> 20:59.530
So when you gonna holler rape?

20:59.908 --> 21:00.738
Me?

21:00.943 --> 21:03.503
Yes, you.
You would, if the time came.

21:03.712 --> 21:04.974
Sure you would.

21:05.714 --> 21:07.511
Malcolm, let me feed you.

21:08.050 --> 21:09.540
Come on.

21:10.385 --> 21:12.114
While they're hot.

21:20.462 --> 21:23.090
I wish your mother and father
could see you now.

21:23.799 --> 21:25.858
And that ofay you're gonna marry.

21:26.068 --> 21:28.127
I sure wish Laura could see us.

22:18.887 --> 22:20.684
Please, Malcolm.

22:21.490 --> 22:23.651
There's nobody around.

22:25.093 --> 22:26.856
No, this ain't right.

22:28.263 --> 22:30.527
-Why?
-Because you--

22:30.732 --> 22:33.724
No, it's because of
the white girl, isn't it?

22:33.935 --> 22:38.395
-It's not because of that.
-Folks say you run around with her.

22:38.607 --> 22:42.407
Save it for Mr. Right. Your
grandmother's smarter than you think.

22:46.014 --> 22:48.539
I'm sorry she raised me that way.

22:54.823 --> 22:56.290
Is your mother alive?

22:56.525 --> 22:57.514
Yes, she's alive.

22:59.061 --> 23:02.030
When I was a kid, I was so poor
I thought "not for sale" ...

23:02.230 --> 23:04.391
...was a brand name.

23:05.067 --> 23:05.965
I did knock.

23:06.168 --> 23:07.635
Did you hear me say, "Come in"?

23:08.837 --> 23:12.000
There's no point in fighting about it.
I'm sorry.

23:12.274 --> 23:15.243
-May I sit down?
-You're nice enough to ask.

23:18.680 --> 23:21.205
It's the same questions, Mrs. Little.

23:21.817 --> 23:25.014
-Since your husband's death...
-Murder. Murder.

23:25.387 --> 23:29.824
...there's a question as to whether you
can raise these children alone.

23:31.259 --> 23:33.284
These are my children.

23:34.996 --> 23:36.657
They're mine.

23:37.732 --> 23:39.324
And they ain't no question.

23:39.534 --> 23:44.471
Sometimes, Mrs. Little, candor
is the only kindness.

23:45.006 --> 23:46.837
All your children are delinquent...

23:47.042 --> 23:50.170
...and one at least,
Malcolm, is a thief.

23:50.378 --> 23:51.037
Get out!

23:51.246 --> 23:54.738
Your control over your
children is nonexistent.

23:54.950 --> 23:56.417
Did you hear me?

23:59.154 --> 24:00.416
You will regret this.

24:00.622 --> 24:04.888
If you don't move through that door,
you'll be past regretting!

24:07.662 --> 24:11.120
<i>We were parceled out, all of us.</i>

24:11.766 --> 24:15.702
<i>I truly believe that if ever</i>
<i>a state agency destroyed a family...</i>

24:16.037 --> 24:17.402
<i>...it destroyed ours.</i>

24:17.973 --> 24:22.910
<i>I was sent to a detention</i>
<i>home and lived at this woman's house.</i>

24:23.178 --> 24:24.611
<i>Mrs. Swerlin.</i>

24:24.813 --> 24:27.941
Boys, this is Malcolm, our new guest.

24:28.350 --> 24:30.045
We'll treat him like a brother.

24:31.186 --> 24:34.553
<i>I was special. The only</i>
<i>colored kid in the class.</i>

24:34.856 --> 24:38.155
<i>I became sort of a mascot,</i>
<i>like a pink poodle.</i>

24:38.827 --> 24:42.422
<i>I got called a nigger so much,</i>
<i>I didn't think it was wrong.</i>

24:42.631 --> 24:44.565
<i>I thought it was my name.</i>

24:45.467 --> 24:48.664
<i>They talked about me like I wasn't</i>
<i>there. Like a pedigreed dog...</i>

24:48.870 --> 24:50.303
<i>...or a horse.</i>

24:51.072 --> 24:52.334
<i>Like I was invisible.</i>

24:52.741 --> 24:56.438
The important thing
is to be realistic.

24:56.645 --> 24:59.136
We all like you here, you know that.

24:59.748 --> 25:01.238
But you're a nigger...

25:01.483 --> 25:04.748
...and a lawyer is no realistic
goal for a nigger.

25:04.953 --> 25:07.547
But why, Mr. Ostrowski?

25:07.822 --> 25:10.188
I gets the best grades in class.

25:10.392 --> 25:13.828
I got voted class president.
I want to be a lawyer.

25:14.029 --> 25:17.157
I want you to think about
something that you can be.

25:17.699 --> 25:20.930
You're good with your hands,
making things.

25:21.503 --> 25:23.494
People would give you work. I would.

25:24.839 --> 25:26.670
Why not become a carpenter?

25:27.409 --> 25:29.934
That's a good profession for a colored.

25:31.079 --> 25:32.774
Wasn't your pa a carpenter?

25:33.949 --> 25:35.678
Jesus was a carpenter.

25:36.685 --> 25:39.916
People like you as a person.
You're doing real well.

25:41.790 --> 25:43.348
Remember what we said.

25:43.792 --> 25:46.352
"Nothing succeeds like success."
Say it.

25:46.561 --> 25:48.961
Nothing succeeds like success.

25:49.164 --> 25:51.064
As long as you're realistic.

25:51.266 --> 25:52.995
It's not the end of the world.

25:55.570 --> 25:57.629
I said, "Don't...

25:58.473 --> 26:00.873
...let them give that boy no pig."

26:01.443 --> 26:03.240
<i>It wasn't the end</i>
<i>of the world for me.</i>

26:03.445 --> 26:05.777
<i>But it was the beginning of the end</i>
<i>for my mother.</i>

26:10.952 --> 26:13.386
<i>A right cross to the jaw by Louis.</i>

26:16.191 --> 26:19.957
<i>Louis takes Conn's head back</i>
<i>with a right uppercut.</i>

26:20.161 --> 26:21.788
<i>Louis hits left and right.</i>

26:21.997 --> 26:25.489
<i>And Conn is down</i>
<i>with a right cross to the jaw!</i>

26:25.734 --> 26:27.292
<i>He's taking the count.</i>

26:27.502 --> 26:30.164
<i>Four, five, six...</i>

26:30.905 --> 26:34.068
<i>...seven. He's on his back.</i>
<i>Eight. Nine.</i>

26:34.342 --> 26:38.210
<i>He's getting up!</i>
<i>The referee says it's all over!</i>

26:41.816 --> 26:44.148
What in hell is going on?

26:44.519 --> 26:45.349
Nothing, Mr. Cooper.

26:45.553 --> 26:47.020
The customer's are hungry.

26:47.522 --> 26:48.989
Soup done finished, Mr. Cooper.

26:49.190 --> 26:50.919
Right, Mr. Charlie.

26:51.526 --> 26:52.891
The name is Mr. Cooper.

26:53.628 --> 26:54.754
Don't you forget it.

26:55.497 --> 26:57.226
Mr. Cooper.

27:00.502 --> 27:02.936
What's the matter with you?
You want me to get fired!

27:03.138 --> 27:04.400
I got a wife and six kids!

27:04.606 --> 27:07.006
Mr. Cooper is good white folk!

27:07.208 --> 27:09.642
You is a young fool!

27:18.186 --> 27:20.882
<i>There'll never be another one like that!</i>

27:22.290 --> 27:23.450
He's done it!

27:23.658 --> 27:25.990
<i>And by a knockout...</i>

27:26.194 --> 27:29.721
<i>...and still the world's</i>
<i>heavyweight champion:</i>

27:29.964 --> 27:32.125
<i>Joe Louis!</i>

27:32.334 --> 27:34.097
Ham and cheese!
Excuse me, sir.

27:34.302 --> 27:37.066
Ham and cheese here! I got coffee.

27:37.272 --> 27:39.900
-Lemon meringue pie.
-Hey, boy!

27:40.175 --> 27:43.508
-Ham and cheese.
-Yes, sir. Best in the house.

27:43.712 --> 27:46.476
-You're pleased with yourself.
-I aims to please, sir.

27:46.681 --> 27:47.807
I'm pleased to aim.

27:48.016 --> 27:49.574
-I like you, boy.
-Thank you.

27:53.621 --> 27:54.451
IKeep the change.

27:54.656 --> 27:56.988
Right, sir!
Ham and cheese!

28:05.166 --> 28:05.996
Harlem!

28:27.856 --> 28:30.620
<i>And here's Joe Lewis,</i>
<i>back in Harlem.</i>

28:31.192 --> 28:33.319
<i>They're celebrating!</i>
<i>They're going crazy!</i>

28:33.528 --> 28:36.725
<i>They're dancing! They're hanging</i>
<i>from street signs!</i>

28:36.931 --> 28:38.660
<i>Everybody's out!</i>

28:39.033 --> 28:42.059
<i>Everyone's having a great time!</i>
<i>Listen to them roar!</i>

29:17.605 --> 29:20.472
<i>Joe's a credit to his race.</i>
<i>What a fine gentleman!</i>

29:20.742 --> 29:22.710
<i>But he's also a fine American.</i>

29:22.911 --> 29:26.244
<i>The Brown Bomber, Joe Louis!</i>

29:28.783 --> 29:29.977
Hey, sugar.

29:30.251 --> 29:32.913
-Slow down. What's your hurry?
-No hurry.

29:33.121 --> 29:34.713
Let me show you something new.

29:35.857 --> 29:37.916
I got gold watches, diamond rings.

29:38.126 --> 29:40.060
Any one of these. Whatever you need.

29:40.395 --> 29:41.327
I don't need that.

29:41.529 --> 29:44.589
You need something, baby.
Whatever you need!

29:44.799 --> 29:46.630
A couple of these
make a player look good.

30:17.899 --> 30:19.230
My man!

30:19.434 --> 30:23.666
-The word is "excuse me," boy.
-"Excuse me" don't shine my shoes.

30:23.872 --> 30:25.567
Then stay out of my way.

30:28.076 --> 30:29.907
Old country nigger.

30:34.349 --> 30:36.112
What you gonna do?

30:42.757 --> 30:43.917
Go home to your mama?

30:54.102 --> 30:58.801
Nigger, don't you ever in your life
say anything against my mother!

31:20.595 --> 31:21.823
Give me a whiskey.

31:31.105 --> 31:32.766
I ordered a single, Jack.

31:32.974 --> 31:35.499
The double's on that gentleman, "Jack."

31:40.181 --> 31:41.341
Who is that?

31:42.250 --> 31:44.343
That's West Indian Archie.

31:44.786 --> 31:46.447
What's his angle?

31:47.689 --> 31:50.283
Some of this, some of that.

32:03.271 --> 32:05.000
Nothing's gonna bite you.

32:06.741 --> 32:08.800
You look like you're new in town.

32:09.010 --> 32:12.138
From what I can see,
you're pretty handy with a bottle.

32:12.347 --> 32:13.177
He had it coming.

32:14.749 --> 32:16.011
Pull up a chair.

32:26.694 --> 32:28.161
What do they call you?

32:28.529 --> 32:29.655
Red.

32:30.498 --> 32:31.726
And I ain't no punk.

32:32.000 --> 32:33.331
You better not be.

32:34.068 --> 32:36.764
Any cat toe you down here,
you stand up or make tracks.

32:36.971 --> 32:38.131
Man live by his rep.

32:38.406 --> 32:39.270
Better believe it.

32:40.775 --> 32:42.265
So what do you do?

32:42.477 --> 32:43.466
Working on the train.

32:45.213 --> 32:46.043
Like that job?

32:46.514 --> 32:50.143
-IKeeps me out of the Army.
-They want you, nothing'll keep you out.

32:50.351 --> 32:51.181
Not this boy.

32:53.121 --> 32:55.589
So I hear tell
you're a good man to know.

32:55.790 --> 32:57.815
-Where you hear that?
-Boston, where I'm from.

32:58.026 --> 32:59.550
IKiss my neck.

32:59.927 --> 33:01.451
I've never been in Beantown.

33:01.663 --> 33:04.496
Like the man said, a man's rep travels.

33:05.533 --> 33:06.864
How about that!

33:09.103 --> 33:10.229
You bullshitting me?

33:10.438 --> 33:13.464
My father told me
never bullshit a West Indian.

33:13.675 --> 33:14.903
Your daddy's West Indian?

33:15.109 --> 33:16.269
My mama.

33:16.944 --> 33:18.707
She's from Grenada.

33:19.013 --> 33:20.275
Grenada.

33:24.218 --> 33:25.082
I like this guy.

33:25.520 --> 33:27.420
I like your country.

33:28.222 --> 33:29.519
Grenada.

33:29.724 --> 33:32.284
Where'd you get them
goddamn vines you got on?

33:32.627 --> 33:34.185
And them shoes?

33:34.495 --> 33:35.325
Oh, my.

33:35.530 --> 33:36.963
We can do something about that.

33:37.165 --> 33:40.430
But he's putting a hurting
on my vision, man!

33:40.635 --> 33:41.795
Relax.

33:42.470 --> 33:43.494
How do I find you?

33:43.705 --> 33:44.899
You can't.

33:45.707 --> 33:47.072
I get ahold of you.

33:47.275 --> 33:49.436
All right, I'll write it down.

33:49.644 --> 33:51.475
Don't ever write anything down.

33:51.679 --> 33:53.408
File it up here.

33:53.748 --> 33:55.147
Like I do.

33:55.983 --> 33:59.384
If the man don't have any paper,
he will never have any proof.

33:59.921 --> 34:00.979
Dig?

34:02.523 --> 34:05.117
Yeah, I dig. Right.

34:10.098 --> 34:11.224
Look me in the face.

34:11.431 --> 34:13.092
Did you just con me?

34:16.003 --> 34:17.094
Yes, sir.

34:17.505 --> 34:18.402
Why?

34:18.606 --> 34:20.130
Because I want in.

34:21.007 --> 34:23.670
It don't take a lot to know
you're already there.

34:23.878 --> 34:25.539
At least he ain't lying.

34:25.746 --> 34:27.179
I have a run to make.

34:27.380 --> 34:29.713
Let me make that run
with you, Mr. Archie.

34:38.926 --> 34:39.915
I like your heart.

34:41.027 --> 34:42.688
I like your style.

34:43.630 --> 34:45.656
You might just do, Mr. Red.

34:45.867 --> 34:49.063
Unless you have to
get back to your train job.

34:49.270 --> 34:51.397
I've told him what to do
with that train.

34:51.606 --> 34:52.833
-When?
-Just now.

34:58.246 --> 34:59.474
All right.

35:00.214 --> 35:01.374
Come with me.

35:01.716 --> 35:03.479
I'm taking you shopping.

35:05.219 --> 35:06.880
Cadillac's the name.

35:07.655 --> 35:09.316
Sammy, man.

35:10.358 --> 35:12.189
-You ready?
-Good.

35:15.596 --> 35:17.496
Button more buttons on the jacket.

35:25.673 --> 35:27.800
You look good.

35:28.075 --> 35:29.337
But you're missing something.

35:29.544 --> 35:30.374
Frisk me.

35:31.045 --> 35:32.979
Go ahead, frisk me.

35:41.622 --> 35:42.782
Nothing, right?

35:48.996 --> 35:50.224
I'm still carrying.

35:50.598 --> 35:52.259
This was my first gun.

35:53.935 --> 35:55.061
Now it's yours.

36:02.610 --> 36:03.474
Thank you.

36:03.678 --> 36:04.940
You wear it...

36:05.780 --> 36:07.213
...wear it so.

36:08.549 --> 36:10.107
Small of the back.

36:11.819 --> 36:13.616
Now you're outfitted.

36:15.523 --> 36:16.751
Ready for the streets?

36:16.958 --> 36:18.289
I'm ready.

36:19.126 --> 36:19.990
Let them come.

36:20.194 --> 36:24.995
Let us now turn to
the Gospel According to St. John.

36:25.266 --> 36:26.528
Chapter 3...

36:26.734 --> 36:29.294
...verse 23.

36:29.804 --> 36:30.634
323.

36:30.838 --> 36:35.741
"And John also was baptizing
in Aenon near Salim...

36:37.178 --> 36:40.477
...because there was much water.

36:41.916 --> 36:44.783
And they came...

36:45.419 --> 36:47.649
...and were baptized."

36:49.957 --> 36:51.481
313.

36:53.361 --> 36:54.328
255.

36:54.795 --> 36:56.558
It got to be 251.

36:57.198 --> 36:58.028
403.

36:58.232 --> 37:00.166
I saw it in my dream.

37:00.368 --> 37:02.802
555.

37:03.004 --> 37:05.495
-What do you know?
-I feel straight.

37:06.607 --> 37:07.904
Your lucky day.

37:08.109 --> 37:09.474
Roll it for me.

37:10.945 --> 37:13.175
I told you, no paper, no trouble.

37:13.648 --> 37:15.115
I'm working on it.

37:16.183 --> 37:18.583
I keep my numbers in my head.

37:18.786 --> 37:22.688
I've never written a number down yet.
Remember that.

37:37.605 --> 37:38.799
Your turn.

37:45.179 --> 37:46.237
Easy.

37:49.884 --> 37:51.112
Easy.

37:53.120 --> 37:53.950
You there?

37:54.155 --> 37:55.417
If I ain't, I'm next door.

37:55.656 --> 37:59.592
Nothing in this world can give you
that real deep cool.

38:00.127 --> 38:01.492
The girl.

38:18.479 --> 38:20.572
About as mellow as I can be.

38:26.020 --> 38:27.112
Cool enough to kill.

38:27.321 --> 38:28.720
I realize that.

38:31.325 --> 38:33.657
-Easy, easy, easy, easy.
-Stick them up.

38:37.498 --> 38:38.465
Archie!

38:41.168 --> 38:42.157
Baby?

38:48.075 --> 38:50.066
Malcolm, you're so funny.

38:52.513 --> 38:54.037
Give me some money, baby.

38:59.553 --> 39:01.248
Come on, baby.

39:01.489 --> 39:03.286
The bitch move too slow.

39:07.261 --> 39:10.526
Sometimes this guy
has a big ugly mouth.

39:10.731 --> 39:12.198
What time is it, baby?

39:13.334 --> 39:15.325
8:21.

39:15.569 --> 39:16.968
I like that. Combinate me.

39:17.638 --> 39:19.299
821.

39:19.507 --> 39:21.202
128.

39:22.443 --> 39:24.001
218.

39:24.245 --> 39:25.337
I'm taking the bet.

39:29.984 --> 39:31.747
Time to reload.

40:19.366 --> 40:22.426
I thought you said we was going
to the movies last night.

40:22.636 --> 40:23.534
You said that.

40:23.804 --> 40:25.738
I'm sorry. I say a lot of things.

40:25.973 --> 40:26.871
I believed you.

40:27.074 --> 40:30.635
Do your job now. Get me a pack
of Lucky Strikes and a cognac.

40:43.791 --> 40:44.951
Daniel come in yet?

40:45.159 --> 40:46.649
Ain't that him?

40:47.428 --> 40:48.417
Gorgeous!

40:49.096 --> 40:52.088
How you been today?
You been waiting long?

40:53.801 --> 40:55.598
Let me look at you.

40:57.304 --> 41:00.762
-I've been missing you today, Laura.
-How you doing, baby?

41:00.975 --> 41:04.638
I'm all right. Copacetic. Great.
Did you work today?

41:04.845 --> 41:07.405
No, baby, I didn't go to work.

41:07.615 --> 41:10.584
-I need a five-spot.
-I gave you 10 this morning.

41:11.051 --> 41:13.485
Give me the goddamn $5!

41:13.687 --> 41:15.211
It ain't the money.
I wanna...

41:15.422 --> 41:17.014
...make sure you're okay.

41:17.224 --> 41:19.454
I gotta pay back this guy.

41:20.127 --> 41:21.321
I'll be right back.

41:22.663 --> 41:24.096
Like last time?

41:24.298 --> 41:26.266
I swear, I'll be right back.

41:26.467 --> 41:28.526
Laura, I love you.

41:37.011 --> 41:38.535
You know that chick?

41:40.614 --> 41:42.479
You a private detective now?

41:42.683 --> 41:43.650
Just asking.

41:43.851 --> 41:45.944
Don't ask me no goddamn questions.

41:46.153 --> 41:48.815
I ask you the questions.
You understand?

41:49.690 --> 41:52.090
-She come in here a lot?
-Almost every night.

41:52.293 --> 41:53.317
With him?

41:54.995 --> 41:57.463
-She know he's high?
-Lf she got eyes, she do.

41:59.733 --> 42:00.757
She ain't hooking?

42:01.135 --> 42:02.966
Not yet, Red.

42:03.504 --> 42:06.632
But the way things are,
he'll turn her out any day now.

42:11.679 --> 42:13.146
You stuck on her?

42:13.347 --> 42:17.010
That's your problem.
You need to mind your own business.

42:20.154 --> 42:21.212
Don't do that!

42:21.422 --> 42:24.220
I wanna talk to you, all right?
Have a seat.

42:33.367 --> 42:35.597
-Don't pay him any mind, hear?
-All right.

42:35.803 --> 42:37.430
-All right?
-I'm all right.

42:44.111 --> 42:46.204
Buy yourself something nice.

42:58.025 --> 42:59.219
Hey, baby.

43:04.531 --> 43:05.964
Give me a light.

43:16.543 --> 43:18.773
You look uptight.
What's the problem?

43:18.979 --> 43:19.968
-No problem.
-Sure?

43:20.180 --> 43:23.149
Everything's all right.
I'm not worrying about it.

43:25.753 --> 43:27.584
I'm thinking about my money.

43:28.088 --> 43:29.885
Six big ones you owe me, right?

43:30.090 --> 43:30.920
What?

43:31.125 --> 43:32.251
821.
It hit, didn't it?

43:32.459 --> 43:34.017
You didn't have 821.

43:34.495 --> 43:37.931
Were you high? I threw the slats
at you, told you to combinate me.

43:38.332 --> 43:39.594
You never had it.

43:39.800 --> 43:42.132
I tell you I did. Sophia was there.

43:42.503 --> 43:44.061
You remember, don't you?

43:44.271 --> 43:45.260
What would she say?

43:46.774 --> 43:48.366
Don't do this.

43:48.575 --> 43:49.599
All right?

43:50.010 --> 43:51.341
All right.

43:53.280 --> 43:55.009
All right, skip it.

43:55.282 --> 43:56.874
But you're slipping, aren't you?

43:57.618 --> 43:59.609
You done slipped.

44:02.790 --> 44:04.348
Archie, wait.

44:15.636 --> 44:17.763
Come on, Archie. Look....

44:18.539 --> 44:21.440
Come on. You want a drink
or something? I'm buying.

44:21.642 --> 44:22.904
I ain't drinking with you.

44:25.479 --> 44:26.605
All right?

44:30.818 --> 44:31.978
Come, Sam.

44:33.554 --> 44:35.385
I'll be right there, man.

44:41.962 --> 44:44.123
Twenty-two years.

44:44.331 --> 44:47.960
Twenty-two years, I never
knowed him to forget a number.

44:48.168 --> 44:49.635
First time for everything.

44:49.837 --> 44:51.702
What are you talking about?

44:51.905 --> 44:56.501
The first thing he'll do is check
with the collector for an oversight.

44:56.744 --> 44:59.770
His rep is on the line. So is yours.

45:00.748 --> 45:04.878
And, Red, if you're lying,
you're a dead man.

45:05.519 --> 45:08.852
Dead, dead, dead.

45:10.824 --> 45:12.314
You go and tell him that.

45:19.533 --> 45:21.262
My man, Red.

45:22.169 --> 45:23.261
Night to you.

45:24.605 --> 45:27.938
I don't understand Archie.
You had the number.

46:01.642 --> 46:04.236
Didn't I tell you never sit
with your back to no door?

46:10.350 --> 46:11.476
You know what?

46:13.587 --> 46:15.316
You're a damn liar.

46:15.589 --> 46:16.886
And so is she.

46:20.494 --> 46:22.121
So you figure to take me...

46:22.329 --> 46:23.921
...you bastard?

46:24.765 --> 46:26.027
I'm taking you.

46:26.233 --> 46:28.565
-So it's you and me?
-That's right.

46:28.769 --> 46:30.361
I'll give you the $ 600.

46:30.571 --> 46:32.300
-I don't want it.
-I'm wearing.

46:32.506 --> 46:35.634
There's three guns on you,
so you take your chances.

46:47.221 --> 46:48.483
Let's walk.

46:56.363 --> 46:58.695
So this is how I'm going out?

46:59.466 --> 47:02.026
-In a toe-down?
-Toe-down, yes.

47:03.070 --> 47:06.039
-Let's go.
-We'll let Billie finish.

47:51.919 --> 47:53.284
<i>Thank you.</i>

47:53.487 --> 47:56.251
<i>Thank you very much. Thank you.</i>

48:18.912 --> 48:19.936
Wake up.

48:21.181 --> 48:22.478
Wake up!

48:24.551 --> 48:26.109
There's somebody out there.

48:29.289 --> 48:30.779
Wake the kids.

48:44.838 --> 48:47.398
Follow me! Wait! Wait!

48:50.277 --> 48:51.107
Go! Go!

48:54.481 --> 48:55.470
Careful!

48:59.119 --> 49:02.680
-Good thing we're all good Christians.
-It's time for you to leave this town.

49:02.889 --> 49:04.015
It's a free country.

49:04.224 --> 49:07.716
We warned you about Garvey preaching!
Stirring up the good niggras!

49:07.928 --> 49:08.952
I ain't a boy!

49:09.162 --> 49:10.789
-I'm a man!
-You're a dead nigger.

49:10.998 --> 49:13.728
And a real man don't hide
behind sheets!

49:13.934 --> 49:16.425
You take these bullets for them sheets!

49:22.976 --> 49:25.444
I know you're a better shot than that.

49:25.746 --> 49:27.338
You should've killed them.

49:27.848 --> 49:29.816
You should've shot them all dead.

49:30.017 --> 49:31.712
I just wanted to scare them.

49:32.619 --> 49:35.213
They won't be around here
bothering us no more.

49:36.757 --> 49:38.952
They won't be here no time soon.

49:39.559 --> 49:40.890
I'm a man!

49:43.030 --> 49:44.224
That'll teach you.

49:51.672 --> 49:52.502
<i>Get a doctor!</i>

49:52.706 --> 49:55.174
<i>He doesn't need a doctor,</i>
<i>he needs a preacher.</i>

49:56.376 --> 49:58.401
I'm glad we got you out of there.

49:58.812 --> 50:01.645
With Archie on your ass,
your name on the wire...

50:01.848 --> 50:04.544
...Boston's the best
goddamn place for you.

50:05.519 --> 50:07.749
We'll take it easy, huh, baby?

50:08.055 --> 50:11.616
I got a place fixed up for us
on Harvard Square. How's that sound?

50:11.892 --> 50:14.622
Sounds good. We'll lay low for a while.

50:15.095 --> 50:18.189
Don't you worry about a thing.
I'll stake you.

50:18.465 --> 50:20.956
I got my band. I'm blowing great sax.

50:21.501 --> 50:23.162
You ain't even heard us play!

50:23.370 --> 50:25.429
<i>Like every hustler, I was trapped.</i>

50:25.639 --> 50:27.766
<i>Cats that hung together</i>
<i>to find security...</i>

50:27.974 --> 50:30.101
<i>...to find an answer, found nothing.</i>

50:30.310 --> 50:32.437
<i>Cats that might've cured cancer....</i>

50:32.646 --> 50:35.513
<i>West Indian Archie might've been</i>
<i>a mathematical genius.</i>

50:35.716 --> 50:38.708
<i>We were all victims</i>
<i>of the American social order.</i>

50:39.052 --> 50:42.681
<i>Until that time, there were</i>
<i>three things I was always afraid of:</i>

50:42.889 --> 50:45.824
<i>A job, a bust and jail.</i>

50:46.026 --> 50:50.360
<i>But I realized then that I wasn't</i>
<i>afraid of anything. I was an animal.</i>

