01:14:52.971 --> 01:14:54.700
That's all right.

01:14:55.307 --> 01:14:56.205
Sure.

01:14:56.942 --> 01:15:00.070
White man throw us a bone
and we're supposed to forget...

01:15:00.279 --> 01:15:01.871
...400 years of oppression.

01:15:02.614 --> 01:15:04.104
Yeah, but a nigger--

01:15:05.184 --> 01:15:07.618
A Negro in the big leagues,
that's something.

01:15:07.786 --> 01:15:11.119
I told you to go behind the words
and dig out the truth.

01:15:11.456 --> 01:15:14.357
They let us sing and dance
and smile...

01:15:14.826 --> 01:15:17.818
...and then they let one
so-called Negro into the majors.

01:15:18.030 --> 01:15:20.624
That doesn't cancel out history's
greatest crime.

01:15:20.899 --> 01:15:23.925
When that grafted, blue-eyed devil
locked us in chains...

01:15:24.136 --> 01:15:27.367
...one hundred million of us,
broke up our families...

01:15:27.573 --> 01:15:28.972
...tortured us...

01:15:29.174 --> 01:15:33.008
...cut us off from our language,
our religion, our history....

01:15:34.780 --> 01:15:37.112
Let me tell you about black history.

01:15:37.316 --> 01:15:39.910
We are the original man.

01:15:40.118 --> 01:15:43.178
The first men on earth were black.
They ruled.

01:15:43.388 --> 01:15:46.186
And there wasn't
a white face anywhere.

01:15:46.491 --> 01:15:49.016
But they teach us
that we swung from trees.

01:15:49.228 --> 01:15:52.561
That's a lie.
Black men never did that.

01:15:52.764 --> 01:15:55.324
We were a race of kings
when the white man...

01:15:55.534 --> 01:15:57.627
...crawled on all fours in Europe.

01:15:57.836 --> 01:15:59.895
Do they know who they are?

01:16:01.907 --> 01:16:04.705
Do you know where you came from?
What's your name?

01:16:04.943 --> 01:16:05.807
Malcolm Little.

01:16:06.979 --> 01:16:10.210
That's the name of the slave masters
that owned your family.

01:16:11.016 --> 01:16:13.007
You don't even know who you are.

01:16:13.218 --> 01:16:15.846
You're nothing.
Less than nothing.

01:16:16.054 --> 01:16:17.544
Who are you?

01:16:21.093 --> 01:16:23.288
Look, I ain't--
Shit!

01:16:27.466 --> 01:16:30.435
All right, I ain't Malcolm Little.
Or Red. Or Satan.

01:16:30.636 --> 01:16:32.160
That's right.
So who are you?

01:16:36.808 --> 01:16:39.140
-I don't know.
-We are a nation...

01:16:39.511 --> 01:16:41.411
...of the tribe of Shabazz...

01:16:41.647 --> 01:16:45.276
...lost in this wilderness called
North America.

01:16:52.958 --> 01:16:54.255
Tribe of Shabazz.

01:16:54.459 --> 01:16:56.893
The merciful Allah
has sent us a messenger...

01:16:57.095 --> 01:16:59.359
...a black man
named Elijah Muhammad.

01:16:59.831 --> 01:17:03.323
He reveals to us the true
knowledge about ourselves.

01:17:03.602 --> 01:17:07.595
He teaches that the true nature
of the original man, the black man...

01:17:07.839 --> 01:17:09.431
...is righteousness.

01:17:09.908 --> 01:17:12.308
If the black man's nature
is righteousness....

01:17:12.511 --> 01:17:15.241
Then the true nature of
the white man is wickedness.

01:17:15.447 --> 01:17:17.005
I knew you'd get it.

01:17:17.282 --> 01:17:21.116
The Honorable Elijah Muhammad teaches
that the white man is a devil.

01:17:21.320 --> 01:17:23.788
I sure met some in my life.

01:17:25.791 --> 01:17:30.023
Elijah Muhammad does not say
that some white men are devils.

01:17:30.462 --> 01:17:33.863
He teaches us that
all white men are devils.

01:17:34.466 --> 01:17:38.630
Have you ever known a good white man?
Think back in all your life.

01:17:39.471 --> 01:17:42.133
Have you ever met one
who wasn't evil?

01:17:50.248 --> 01:17:51.943
<i>The body is a sacred temple...</i>

01:17:52.150 --> 01:17:54.414
<i>...it must be purified.</i>

01:17:55.987 --> 01:17:58.820
I will not touch
the white man's poison:

01:17:59.024 --> 01:18:00.423
His drugs...

01:18:00.859 --> 01:18:02.326
...his liquor...

01:18:03.328 --> 01:18:05.523
...his swine...

01:18:05.731 --> 01:18:06.823
...his women.

01:18:07.666 --> 01:18:10.328
A Muslim must be strikingly upright...

01:18:10.569 --> 01:18:12.366
...an outstanding example...

01:18:12.571 --> 01:18:16.029
...so that those in the darkness
can see the power of the light.

01:18:18.176 --> 01:18:21.407
I will not commit
adultery or fornication.

01:18:23.014 --> 01:18:24.641
I will not lie...

01:18:24.850 --> 01:18:26.579
...cheat or steal.

01:18:27.919 --> 01:18:30.353
But the key to Islam is submission.

01:18:34.926 --> 01:18:38.384
That is why five times daily,
we turn to Mecca to pray...

01:18:38.597 --> 01:18:41.088
...to bend our knees in submission.

01:18:44.703 --> 01:18:47.035
I can't do that, Brother Baines.

01:18:47.639 --> 01:18:49.834
The lost, found,
must bend their knees...

01:18:50.041 --> 01:18:51.531
...to admit their guilt.

01:18:51.743 --> 01:18:56.442
To implore Allah's forgiveness
is the hardest thing on earth.

01:19:02.387 --> 01:19:04.719
The hardest and the greatest.

01:19:09.561 --> 01:19:12.394
I don't know
what I would say to Allah.

01:19:12.964 --> 01:19:15.398
Have you ever bent your knees?

01:19:18.236 --> 01:19:20.227
Yes, when I was...

01:19:21.306 --> 01:19:23.797
...picking a lock
to rob someone's house.

01:19:24.009 --> 01:19:25.271
Tell Allah that.

01:19:36.922 --> 01:19:40.915
You can grovel and crawl for sin
but not to save your soul?

01:19:41.126 --> 01:19:43.151
Pick the lock.
Pick it.

01:19:43.762 --> 01:19:45.423
I want to.

01:19:49.134 --> 01:19:51.068
God knows I want to.

01:20:02.047 --> 01:20:05.813
<i>I received a letter that day</i>
<i>from the Honorable Elijah Muhammad.</i>

01:20:06.084 --> 01:20:08.279
<i>The dear Holy Apostle</i>
<i>wrote to me...</i>

01:20:08.487 --> 01:20:11.320
<i>...a nobody, a junkie, a pimp</i>
<i>and a convict.</i>

01:20:11.523 --> 01:20:14.492
<i>I have come to give you...</i>

01:20:14.926 --> 01:20:18.589
<i>...something which can</i>
<i>never be taken away from you.</i>

01:20:18.830 --> 01:20:23.767
<i>I bring to you</i>
<i>a sense of your own worth...</i>

01:20:24.603 --> 01:20:27.367
<i>...the worth of one human being.</i>

01:20:27.572 --> 01:20:30.063
<i>The knowledge of self.</i>

01:20:30.275 --> 01:20:34.575
<i>It was like a blinding light. I was</i>
<i>aware that he was in the room with me.</i>

01:20:35.113 --> 01:20:38.082
<i>He wore a dark suit,</i>
<i>and on his face I saw a wisdom...</i>

01:20:38.283 --> 01:20:41.946
<i>...and pain so old and deep</i>
<i>that I could scarcely look at him.</i>

01:20:42.954 --> 01:20:45.718
<i>But I knew I wasn't dreaming.</i>
<i>He was there with me.</i>

01:20:45.924 --> 01:20:47.789
<i>I tell you...</i>

01:20:49.194 --> 01:20:52.527
<i>...the most dangerous creation</i>
<i>in the world...</i>

01:20:52.864 --> 01:20:55.128
<i>...in any society...</i>

01:20:55.700 --> 01:20:58.294
<i>...is the man with nothing to lose.</i>

01:20:58.537 --> 01:21:03.474
<i>You do not need 10 such men</i>
<i>to change the world.</i>

01:21:04.376 --> 01:21:06.367
<i>One will do.</i>

01:21:07.479 --> 01:21:10.380
<i>The earth belongs to us...</i>

01:21:10.582 --> 01:21:11.981
<i>...the black man.</i>

01:21:12.317 --> 01:21:14.683
<i>And whatever is around it...</i>

01:21:14.886 --> 01:21:17.878
<i>...or on it, or in it...</i>

01:21:18.156 --> 01:21:20.181
<i>...belongs to us.</i>

01:21:20.392 --> 01:21:22.553
<i>And then as suddenly as he came...</i>

01:21:22.761 --> 01:21:23.887
<i>...he was gone.</i>

01:21:26.031 --> 01:21:27.589
<i>And then I could do it.</i>

01:21:30.502 --> 01:21:31.799
<i>We're taught that Paul...</i>

01:21:32.003 --> 01:21:35.370
<i>...on the road to Damascus,</i>
<i>heard the voice of Christ.</i>

01:21:35.640 --> 01:21:38.609
<i>He was so smitten by the truth</i>
<i>that he fell from his horse.</i>

01:21:38.810 --> 01:21:40.971
<i>Now, I don't liken myself to Paul...</i>

01:21:41.246 --> 01:21:42.907
<i>...but I do understand.</i>

01:21:44.482 --> 01:21:46.040
<i>You see, it happened to me.</i>

01:21:46.251 --> 01:21:47.343
Why me?

01:21:49.154 --> 01:21:53.818
<i>Dear Brother Malcolm: I am back</i>
<i>in the bosom of Islam, praise Allah.</i>

01:21:54.092 --> 01:21:57.357
<i>We don't have much,</i>
