01:28:18.776 --> 01:28:21.768
It's time for black men and women
to stand up...

01:28:21.980 --> 01:28:24.005
...and take control of our dollars.

01:28:24.215 --> 01:28:28.049
It's time for us to use our dollars
for our liberation.

01:28:28.252 --> 01:28:31.710
We can do what everyone else can
if we become producers...

01:28:31.923 --> 01:28:34.892
...and if we become
the masters of our own destiny.

01:28:35.093 --> 01:28:37.823
We can have wool from sheep
just like anyone else.

01:28:38.029 --> 01:28:39.929
But where are our clothing stores?

01:28:40.131 --> 01:28:44.431
We can get milk from cows,
but where are our grocery stores?

01:28:44.635 --> 01:28:48.503
We need to control our dollars!
We need to control our destiny!

01:28:48.706 --> 01:28:51.800
The only thing they respect
is our dollars!

01:28:54.012 --> 01:28:56.344
--The so-called freedom
we should have.

01:28:56.581 --> 01:28:58.742
The Statue of Liberty
stands like this.

01:28:58.950 --> 01:29:02.113
For us, it may as well say,
"Stop, don't come no further."

01:29:03.688 --> 01:29:05.485
"Don't come no further."

01:29:05.690 --> 01:29:07.817
Brothers and sisters,
I want you to....

01:29:08.026 --> 01:29:10.119
I want you to come down
to the temple.

01:29:10.328 --> 01:29:11.989
Oh, I'm so surprised!

01:29:12.196 --> 01:29:15.290
I'm so surprised.
You all been in church two hours...

01:29:15.500 --> 01:29:19.231
...expecting to see heaven,
but you're still here on earth.

01:29:19.437 --> 01:29:22.031
Why don't you come on down
to the temple at 2:00?

01:29:22.240 --> 01:29:24.470
You'll hear truth,
the black man's truth.

01:29:24.675 --> 01:29:28.577
No, you can't deny it.
You been on your knees for hours...

01:29:28.780 --> 01:29:31.044
...begging some God to help you
in the hereafter.

01:29:31.249 --> 01:29:34.776
But the hereafter is right now.
The hereafter is here and now.

01:29:34.986 --> 01:29:36.715
Let me talk to you, brother.

01:29:36.921 --> 01:29:39.788
I know you're a smart man
and a wise man.

01:29:39.991 --> 01:29:40.923
You look good.

01:29:41.125 --> 01:29:44.583
Now, you're in church every day,
praying to this God.

01:29:44.829 --> 01:29:46.888
But these so-called white Christians...

01:29:47.098 --> 01:29:49.498
...hang our black Christians
from trees.

01:29:49.834 --> 01:29:53.292
This man hates you.
He doesn't do anything for you.

01:29:53.504 --> 01:29:55.836
He tells you to foam at
the mouth and sing...

01:29:56.040 --> 01:29:58.440
...and hope for something
in the hereafter.

01:29:58.643 --> 01:29:59.905
We can have it now.

01:30:00.111 --> 01:30:02.341
-Come on down, 2:00.
-See you later.

01:30:02.547 --> 01:30:05.778
As-Salaam-Alaikum
That means, "Peace be unto you."

01:30:05.983 --> 01:30:09.043
We have two children.
Carla, who's two, and....

01:30:09.253 --> 01:30:11.983
Don't be ashamed when I call
you black. You are.

01:30:12.190 --> 01:30:15.182
You're black and you're beautiful.
Black is beautiful.

01:30:15.393 --> 01:30:18.760
You don't have to come here
begging these folks for a job.

01:30:18.963 --> 01:30:21.932
You can wash their clothes
and scrub floors for them.

01:30:22.133 --> 01:30:25.330
You can rock their little
brats to sleep your whole life.

01:30:25.536 --> 01:30:27.094
You'll still end up poor.

01:30:27.305 --> 01:30:30.297
Yet you're here on the auction block
being examined...

01:30:30.508 --> 01:30:32.669
...like you're a horse or a slave.

01:30:32.877 --> 01:30:35.903
You see this here?
This is who you are. Beautiful.

01:30:36.114 --> 01:30:39.709
Your beautiful black selves,
with pride and dignity.

01:30:42.320 --> 01:30:45.346
I'd also expect you to work one
Saturday every month...

01:30:45.556 --> 01:30:48.286
...and occasionally in the evening--

01:30:53.998 --> 01:30:57.934
See, these are the questions
you and I have to ask:

01:30:58.136 --> 01:30:59.603
"How did we get this mind?"

01:30:59.804 --> 01:31:03.638
You're not an American, but an African
who happens to be in America.

01:31:03.908 --> 01:31:05.637
You must understand the difference.

01:31:05.843 --> 01:31:09.335
We didn't come over on the <i>Niña,</i>
the <i>Pinta</i> and the whatchamacallit.

01:31:09.580 --> 01:31:13.346
We didn't land on Plymouth Rock.
Plymouth Rock landed on us.

01:31:13.718 --> 01:31:16.243
Landed right on top of us.

01:31:18.856 --> 01:31:19.823
Shorty?

01:31:20.925 --> 01:31:22.483
Is that you, brother?

01:31:22.693 --> 01:31:26.629
Now, this is exactly what I'm talking
about, the slave mentality...

01:31:26.831 --> 01:31:27.889
...the slave mind.

01:31:28.099 --> 01:31:29.999
This brother and I had
the slave mind.

01:31:30.201 --> 01:31:33.102
We used to rob together.
We slept with white women.

01:31:33.304 --> 01:31:34.965
We even went to prison together.

01:31:35.173 --> 01:31:38.199
Don't be surprised.
Some of you are still in prison...

01:31:38.442 --> 01:31:39.807
...prisons of your mind.

01:31:40.011 --> 01:31:41.706
Stand up, brother.
Come on.

01:31:43.281 --> 01:31:45.146
The brother's a little shy.

01:31:45.349 --> 01:31:47.510
Come on, brother.
Give me a hug.

01:31:49.554 --> 01:31:51.112
That's all right, brother.

01:31:52.590 --> 01:31:54.558
Look, he's still got his hair fried.

01:31:54.759 --> 01:31:57.523
That's the slave mind.

01:31:57.728 --> 01:32:00.856
Red, that's the best preacher hype
I ever did hear.

01:32:01.065 --> 01:32:02.930
No hype, brother.
It's the truth.

01:32:03.134 --> 01:32:05.193
Come back to the temple
and hear more.

01:32:05.403 --> 01:32:07.166
I can't pay that shit no mind.

01:32:07.371 --> 01:32:09.771
You need to pay it all your mind.
What's left.

01:32:09.974 --> 01:32:12.374
Take it easy.
This is me. Shorty.

01:32:12.577 --> 01:32:14.272
Let's go around the corner....

01:32:15.813 --> 01:32:19.146
No, sir. Not anymore.
I've been clean for eight years.

01:32:19.350 --> 01:32:20.977
-Eight years?
-Eight years.

01:32:21.185 --> 01:32:25.212
My trouble is, I love pigs feet
and white women too much.

01:32:25.489 --> 01:32:27.719
So I damn sure can't be no Muslim.

01:32:27.925 --> 01:32:31.827
That's because you're lost, brother.
That's because you're lost.

01:32:32.330 --> 01:32:33.991
But we can find you.

01:32:38.269 --> 01:32:40.260
What do you hear about
the old gang?

01:32:40.838 --> 01:32:42.328
You heard about Sammy?

01:32:42.640 --> 01:32:47.077
<i>Dead. Knocked over in bed with</i>
<i>a chick 25 years younger than he was.</i>

01:32:47.278 --> 01:32:52.215
<i>Had 25 grand in his pocket, also.</i>
Guess it was his lucky number.

01:32:52.750 --> 01:32:55.344
What about....

01:32:55.553 --> 01:32:56.747
What was his name?

01:32:56.954 --> 01:32:58.387
Cadillac?

01:32:58.589 --> 01:32:59.647
Gone too?

01:32:59.857 --> 01:33:04.021
<i>Hooked on heroin. Been in and out</i>
<i>of Lexington five or six times.</i>

01:33:04.228 --> 01:33:05.058
Sophia?

01:33:05.263 --> 01:33:07.663
Still happily married
to that rich ofay.

01:33:07.865 --> 01:33:10.026
-<i>She married him?</i>
-<i>She married him.</i>

01:33:10.468 --> 01:33:11.958
<i>Went for the money.</i>

01:33:12.270 --> 01:33:14.738
-<i>The money.</i>
-<i>Thank you, honey.</i>

01:33:16.307 --> 01:33:18.104
I haven't seen
West Indian Archie.

01:33:18.309 --> 01:33:21.176
<i>Grapevine says</i>
<i>he's living in the Bronx.</i>

01:33:21.379 --> 01:33:23.279
<i>If you wanna call that living.</i>

01:33:23.481 --> 01:33:25.244
<i>It's been good seeing you.</i>

01:33:25.449 --> 01:33:27.041
<i>Same here, Red.</i>

01:33:33.457 --> 01:33:38.156
Get the hell away from me, bitch!

01:33:41.699 --> 01:33:44.167
I'll pay you tomorrow!

01:33:58.683 --> 01:33:59.843
How you doing, Archie?

01:34:00.351 --> 01:34:02.182
My man, Red.

01:34:04.855 --> 01:34:06.345
Come here, man.

01:34:10.695 --> 01:34:12.925
No, don't get up.
It's all right.

01:34:20.705 --> 01:34:22.036
Is...

01:34:24.108 --> 01:34:25.939
...really you, Red?

01:34:27.044 --> 01:34:28.443
Yes, it's me.

01:34:32.883 --> 01:34:34.612
I came to...

01:34:35.453 --> 01:34:37.045
...just to thank you...

01:34:38.889 --> 01:34:40.584
...for saving my life.

01:34:40.791 --> 01:34:44.352
When I think back to when
we were in Harlem trying to...

01:34:44.695 --> 01:34:46.094
...gun each other down--

01:34:46.297 --> 01:34:48.527
I wasn't going to shoot you, man.

01:34:50.134 --> 01:34:51.123
It was...

01:34:51.769 --> 01:34:53.293
...just my rep.

01:34:54.238 --> 01:34:55.227
You know?

01:34:56.674 --> 01:34:59.472
All I had was my rep.

01:35:01.145 --> 01:35:02.237
But now...

01:35:04.615 --> 01:35:05.912
...you tell me this.

01:35:06.417 --> 01:35:09.580
You did really have that number?

01:35:11.455 --> 01:35:13.252
I don't know, Archie....

01:35:13.591 --> 01:35:15.616
I don't remember,
and it's not important.

01:35:15.826 --> 01:35:19.660
The important thing now
is to get you back on your feet.

01:35:21.098 --> 01:35:23.589
You know, I have some angles...

01:35:25.569 --> 01:35:27.366
...ain't been figured yet.

01:35:35.346 --> 01:35:36.472
It's all right.

01:35:41.485 --> 01:35:43.510
Help me with my arm.

01:35:44.989 --> 01:35:47.287
I need to exercise my arm.

01:35:54.799 --> 01:35:56.096
That's better?

01:35:56.300 --> 01:35:58.598
Yep.
It feels good.

01:35:58.803 --> 01:36:00.862
Good.

01:36:04.875 --> 01:36:09.278
<i>What happened to our women?</i>
<i>They could've been doctors, lawyers...</i>

01:36:09.480 --> 01:36:12.677
<i>...or teachers or mothers.</i>
<i>Who'll raise our children?</i>

01:36:12.883 --> 01:36:14.441
<i>What happened to our men?</i>

01:36:14.652 --> 01:36:18.850
<i>Men who could've been mathematicians,</i>
<i>electricians, physicians.</i>

01:36:19.056 --> 01:36:21.422
<i>What's the little boy gonna do...</i>

01:36:21.625 --> 01:36:24.685
<i>...when he's looking for his father</i>
<i>who's in jail?</i>

01:36:25.029 --> 01:36:26.291
<i>What'll the girl do...</i>

01:36:26.497 --> 01:36:30.331
<i>...when she's looking for her mother</i>
<i>who's out selling herself?</i>

01:36:30.534 --> 01:36:35.369
<i>I'm telling you, that devil has made</i>
<i>dead souls out of you and I.</i>

01:36:35.773 --> 01:36:37.365
<i>You're dead, spiritually.</i>

01:36:37.575 --> 01:36:41.306
<i>You're dead to the knowledge</i>
<i>of yourself and your people...</i>

01:36:41.512 --> 01:36:43.810
<i>...and to the knowledge</i>
<i>of your God.</i>

01:36:44.014 --> 01:36:47.142
<i>Why, he should get down on his knees.</i>

01:36:47.351 --> 01:36:48.477
<i>He should beg our mercy.</i>

01:36:49.353 --> 01:36:50.911
Oh, my brothers and sisters...

01:36:51.121 --> 01:36:53.749
...his kind has committed
God's greatest crime...

01:36:53.958 --> 01:36:57.485
...against your and my kind
every day of his life!

01:36:57.695 --> 01:37:01.392
He should get on his knees
and say he's committed a crime.

01:37:01.599 --> 01:37:02.657
But does he do that?

01:37:02.867 --> 01:37:05.995
Does he do that?
No, no, he scorns you.

01:37:06.203 --> 01:37:08.398
He splits your head with
his nightstick.

01:37:08.606 --> 01:37:11.200
He busts you in the head
with his billy club.

01:37:11.408 --> 01:37:13.069
And he calls you a nigger...

01:37:13.277 --> 01:37:17.145
...a coon. That's what he says to you.
"Boy!" "Nigger!"

01:37:17.348 --> 01:37:19.339
Four hundred years is long enough.

01:37:19.550 --> 01:37:23.008
You've sat down and laid down
and bowed down for 400 years.

01:37:23.220 --> 01:37:26.917
I think it's time to stand up.
I think it's time to stand up.

01:37:27.124 --> 01:37:28.955
-We're with you!
-All right.

01:37:29.159 --> 01:37:30.091
Bless you.

01:37:37.101 --> 01:37:39.797
Glory! My Lord!
Praise Him!

01:37:54.018 --> 01:37:55.883
Yes, sir.
Next Wednesday, 8:00.

01:37:56.086 --> 01:37:57.485
I'll see you there.

01:37:58.756 --> 01:38:00.781
Brother Baines?
Excuse me, sister.

01:38:00.991 --> 01:38:04.051
Do you think we can get
a loudspeaker set up outside?

01:38:04.261 --> 01:38:05.489
I'm sure we can.

01:38:05.696 --> 01:38:07.789
Brother Malcolm,
this is Sister Betty.

01:38:07.998 --> 01:38:10.728
She lectures our Muslim women
on hygiene and diet.

01:38:10.935 --> 01:38:14.063
She stresses care for the body
and regular eating habits.

01:38:14.338 --> 01:38:15.532
Good.

01:38:15.739 --> 01:38:18.503
-As-Salaam-Alaikum.
-Alaikum-Salaam, sister.

01:38:20.244 --> 01:38:21.734
Brother Minister...

01:38:21.946 --> 01:38:25.382
...the sister wonders if you know
what Harriet Tubman did...

01:38:25.583 --> 01:38:28.575
...between taking souls to the
Promised Land?

01:38:28.786 --> 01:38:31.016
No. What's that, sister?

01:38:32.356 --> 01:38:33.789
She ate.

01:38:37.194 --> 01:38:38.525
Excuse me.

01:38:47.638 --> 01:38:48.764
She's interesting.

01:38:48.973 --> 01:38:52.340
Minister, I was hoping
you'd come and speak to my class.

01:38:53.611 --> 01:38:55.476
Yes, I'll speak to your class.

01:38:56.313 --> 01:38:59.077
-But I'm a hard man on the women.
-Are you?

01:38:59.817 --> 01:39:02.342
We must be very careful
when it comes to women.

01:39:02.553 --> 01:39:04.885
Too many of our women...

01:39:05.956 --> 01:39:07.947
...have too much
of the devil in them.

01:39:08.359 --> 01:39:10.486
Bleaching and dyeing...

01:39:12.029 --> 01:39:14.327
...and ironing their hair.

01:39:15.332 --> 01:39:19.359
Running around
in the streets half-naked.

01:39:21.438 --> 01:39:22.700
Talking too much.

01:39:22.906 --> 01:39:24.533
Listening to the wrong men...

01:39:24.742 --> 01:39:28.303
...making them
deceitful, untrustworthy, fresh.

01:39:28.512 --> 01:39:30.844
And you men are to blame too.

01:39:31.048 --> 01:39:34.916
We don't protect, we don't value,
we don't even support them.

01:39:35.486 --> 01:39:37.181
See, the building of
a new nation...

01:39:38.255 --> 01:39:40.086
...begins with the woman.

01:39:40.591 --> 01:39:42.354
Because the mother...

01:39:42.760 --> 01:39:45.194
...is the first teacher of the child.

01:39:45.429 --> 01:39:49.126
The message she gives that child,
the child gives to the world.

01:39:49.933 --> 01:39:53.334
When it comes to choosing a mate...

01:39:53.871 --> 01:39:58.240
...Samson, the strongest man
that ever lived, was destroyed...

01:39:58.442 --> 01:40:00.933
...by the woman
that slept in his arms.

01:40:01.145 --> 01:40:03.613
Should I tell my sisters, then...

01:40:03.881 --> 01:40:06.281
...that we don't believe in marriage?

01:40:06.483 --> 01:40:09.077
No, we don't oppose marriage.

01:40:09.286 --> 01:40:11.117
We're not Catholic priests.

01:40:11.321 --> 01:40:13.084
We don't believe in celibacy.

01:40:13.290 --> 01:40:15.554
Mr. Muhammad teaches
that if a woman...

01:40:15.759 --> 01:40:18.489
...is the right height
and complexion for a man--

01:40:18.696 --> 01:40:20.027
If she's...

01:40:20.264 --> 01:40:21.993
...half the man's age, plus seven.

01:40:24.331 --> 01:40:25.855
And if...

01:40:26.066 --> 01:40:30.696
...she understands that man's
essential nature is strong...

01:40:31.038 --> 01:40:33.063
...and she's
willing to support that.

01:40:33.607 --> 01:40:35.131
And if she...

01:40:35.642 --> 01:40:38.076
...can sew and cook and...

01:40:38.645 --> 01:40:39.907
...loves children...

01:40:40.113 --> 01:40:42.172
...and stays out of trouble....

01:40:42.382 --> 01:40:45.442
I think you've made your points,
Brother Minister.

01:40:45.652 --> 01:40:46.619
Good.

01:40:46.820 --> 01:40:49.288
You haven't any time for marriage.

01:40:51.091 --> 01:40:54.549
So what I'll do is
write the chapters down for you...

01:40:54.928 --> 01:40:55.792
All right.

01:40:55.996 --> 01:40:59.295
...as well as the New Testament
chapters in St. Matthew.

01:40:59.600 --> 01:41:00.897
Brother Minister....

01:41:01.101 --> 01:41:03.865
I hope you'll still
come visit my class, though.

01:41:04.071 --> 01:41:07.063
No, I'd love to come to your class.
I love to teach.

01:41:07.407 --> 01:41:10.899
I love sharing. This is the wonderful
thing about Mr. Muhammad:

01:41:11.111 --> 01:41:15.445
When he gives you this knowledge,
you can't help but share it--

01:41:15.649 --> 01:41:18.413
Excuse me, Brother Minister...

01:41:18.619 --> 01:41:20.314
...would it be okay if we...

01:41:20.520 --> 01:41:22.385
...just sat down for a moment?

01:41:22.589 --> 01:41:25.080
It's a big building and....

01:41:26.960 --> 01:41:30.225
Sister, I'm sorry.
I've had you on your feet all day.

01:41:31.098 --> 01:41:32.258
My mistake.

01:41:32.466 --> 01:41:34.696
You've been on your feet for days.

01:41:35.736 --> 01:41:39.172
And you didn't even finish your salad.

01:41:41.708 --> 01:41:44.108
So let's talk about you
for a change.

01:41:44.645 --> 01:41:45.976
How tall are you?

01:41:47.547 --> 01:41:48.707
Why do you ask?

01:41:48.916 --> 01:41:50.144
Idle question.

01:41:50.717 --> 01:41:55.120
Well, if it's just an idle question,
I hope I'm not forced to answer.

01:41:56.123 --> 01:41:58.785
No, I won't force you.

01:42:03.830 --> 01:42:07.425
Brother Baines says that
I'm tall enough for a tall man.

01:42:07.634 --> 01:42:09.465
He's briefed you also?

01:42:11.738 --> 01:42:13.296
How old are you, sister?

01:42:14.107 --> 01:42:17.372
You know, there are
a few things about women...

01:42:17.577 --> 01:42:19.568
...that you don't understand.

01:42:19.780 --> 01:42:23.079
Some of us, we're
quite possessive, very vain...

01:42:23.817 --> 01:42:27.150
...and persistent when
we've set our mind to something.

01:42:27.688 --> 01:42:30.156
What have you set your mind to?

01:42:32.292 --> 01:42:34.021
Being a good Muslim...

01:42:34.861 --> 01:42:36.590
...a good nurse...

01:42:38.365 --> 01:42:39.923
...and a good wife.

01:42:40.867 --> 01:42:42.164
Brother Malcolm?

01:42:42.369 --> 01:42:43.893
-Excuse me.
-Certainly.

01:42:44.104 --> 01:42:46.732
Brother Johnson was attacked
by the police.

01:42:48.775 --> 01:42:49.639
Excuse me.

01:42:49.843 --> 01:42:51.743
-A scuffle!
-He was just watching.

01:42:51.945 --> 01:42:55.244
-The cop said, "Move on!"
-He didn't move quick enough for him.

01:42:55.449 --> 01:42:57.679
Crack! He was bleeding
like a stuck hog.

01:42:57.884 --> 01:43:00.045
So what you gonna do?

01:43:00.754 --> 01:43:03.655
He'll rap a little.
He's a Muslim!

01:43:03.857 --> 01:43:06.792
But you ain't gonna do nothing
but make a speech.

01:43:07.260 --> 01:43:10.525
Muslims talk a good game,
but they never do nothing...

01:43:10.998 --> 01:43:13.728
...unless somebody bothers Muslims.

01:43:34.521 --> 01:43:36.284
We demand to see Brother Johnson.

01:43:36.490 --> 01:43:38.287
Who the hell are you?

01:43:38.492 --> 01:43:40.392
The minister
of Muslim Temple No. 7.

01:43:40.594 --> 01:43:42.255
Never heard of you.

01:43:42.496 --> 01:43:43.963
-Where is he?
-Not here.

01:43:44.164 --> 01:43:46.394
Wait a second.
What is your name?

01:43:46.600 --> 01:43:48.898
Don't worry about what my name is.

01:43:49.102 --> 01:43:52.868
Two witnesses saw Johnson brought here
beat up, but not brought out.

01:43:53.073 --> 01:43:56.201
You didn't hear the sergeant?
Outside!

01:43:56.410 --> 01:43:58.935
I suggest you look outside
that window.

01:44:10.257 --> 01:44:11.747
Jimmy, come here a second.

01:44:11.958 --> 01:44:14.358
We intend to see Brother Johnson.

01:44:15.162 --> 01:44:16.322
Who the hell are they?

01:44:16.530 --> 01:44:18.896
They're brothers of Brother Johnson.

01:44:23.003 --> 01:44:25.130
Eddie, let me take a look
at that blotter.

01:44:35.148 --> 01:44:37.514
We got a Muslim.
Relief must've put it down.

01:44:37.717 --> 01:44:39.708
-Must have.
-But you can't see him.

01:44:39.920 --> 01:44:42.855
-Because you ain't his lawyer.
-No lawyer, no see.

01:44:43.056 --> 01:44:47.425
Until I'm satisfied that Johnson
is receiving proper medical care...

01:44:47.627 --> 01:44:49.288
...nobody will move.

01:45:04.344 --> 01:45:06.312
Get an ambulance. Now!

01:45:24.965 --> 01:45:27.058
Break it up. You got what you wanted.

01:45:27.267 --> 01:45:29.735
No, I'm not satisfied.

01:45:30.770 --> 01:45:31.668
To the hospital.

01:47:31.424 --> 01:47:34.587
We want justice!
We want justice!

01:47:35.295 --> 01:47:36.762
All right, that's enough.

01:47:36.963 --> 01:47:38.624
Move these people out of here.

01:47:38.832 --> 01:47:43.326
Fruit of Islam are disciplined men.
They haven't broken any laws...yet.

01:47:43.536 --> 01:47:44.434
What about them?

01:47:44.638 --> 01:47:46.230
That's your headache.

01:47:46.439 --> 01:47:48.669
But if Brother Johnson dies,
I pity you.

01:47:50.110 --> 01:47:51.077
Doctor?

01:47:51.278 --> 01:47:53.746
He'll live. He's getting
the best care we have.

01:47:53.947 --> 01:47:55.073
-Thank you.
-Certainly.

01:47:56.216 --> 01:47:57.877
All right, okay.

01:47:58.285 --> 01:47:59.946
Now, let's disperse this mob!

01:48:52.806 --> 01:48:55.707
That's too much power
for one man to have.

01:48:55.909 --> 01:48:58.969
Brother Minister, I'm ready
to take some heads.

01:48:59.179 --> 01:49:01.409
We gotta do something
to put fear in those devils.

01:49:01.614 --> 01:49:05.880
I'm ready to do something also. The
word out of Chicago was to be patient.

01:49:06.086 --> 01:49:08.953
-I'm tired of being patient.
-Then you get on the phone--

01:49:09.756 --> 01:49:13.021
You get on the phone, call Chicago
and let Mr. Muhammad know.

01:49:30.276 --> 01:49:31.743
Have a seat, son.

01:49:35.382 --> 01:49:37.646
The only thing I like integrated...

01:49:39.152 --> 01:49:39.982
...is my coffee.

01:49:42.155 --> 01:49:43.679
What can I do for you?

01:49:47.026 --> 01:49:48.653
Well, Mr. X...

01:49:50.029 --> 01:49:51.656
...my name is Benjamin.

01:49:52.232 --> 01:49:54.223
I was out there tonight.

01:49:54.734 --> 01:49:56.167
Take it easy now.

01:49:56.536 --> 01:49:59.004
And I saw what it is that you did.

01:49:59.205 --> 01:50:01.969
The way you talked
to them policeman and all.

01:50:06.346 --> 01:50:07.836
Well, Mr. X...

01:50:10.450 --> 01:50:12.315
...I want to be a Muslim.

01:50:12.685 --> 01:50:15.415
I ain't never seen a nigger--
I mean...

01:50:15.688 --> 01:50:17.019
...colored person--

01:50:18.925 --> 01:50:20.017
Negro...

01:50:21.027 --> 01:50:23.325
...talk to no police like that before.

01:50:23.530 --> 01:50:26.465
And you want to be Muslim?
Join the Nation Of Islam?

01:50:26.666 --> 01:50:29.567
You know what that means?
To be a Muslim?

01:50:31.671 --> 01:50:32.797
Do you?

01:50:36.376 --> 01:50:39.345
No, not exactly.
But I wanna be one.

01:50:39.712 --> 01:50:40.770
Just like you.

01:50:40.980 --> 01:50:44.939
You shouldn't join any organization
unless you know what it's about.

01:50:51.624 --> 01:50:52.921
Thank you.

01:50:54.594 --> 01:50:56.926
You shouldn't give up
so easily either.

01:50:58.965 --> 01:51:02.230
We could use more young warriors
like yourself.

01:51:02.469 --> 01:51:04.903
Come on by the temple
next Wednesday, 8:00.

01:51:05.138 --> 01:51:06.332
8:00 sharp.

01:51:06.539 --> 01:51:08.370
Yes, sir. 8:00 sharp.

01:51:08.575 --> 01:51:11.874
Thank you, Mr. X. And I won't
make you out a liar either.

01:51:12.078 --> 01:51:13.306
I don't think you will.

01:51:26.493 --> 01:51:27.926
Tonight, I shall...

01:51:28.428 --> 01:51:32.387
...introduce you
as my national minister.

01:51:33.633 --> 01:51:36.101
It will be a difficult task.

01:51:36.503 --> 01:51:38.095
Your assignment...

01:51:38.938 --> 01:51:41.600
...is to build temples
all over this nation.

01:51:42.709 --> 01:51:44.802
More work than you've ever done.

01:51:45.011 --> 01:51:46.069
Yes, sir.

01:51:46.279 --> 01:51:48.304
You will be in the public eye.

01:51:48.515 --> 01:51:51.143
Beware of them cameras.

01:51:53.520 --> 01:51:54.851
Them cameras are...

01:51:55.622 --> 01:51:57.852
...bad as any narcotic.

01:52:00.793 --> 01:52:03.489
White devil will be watching
your every step.

01:52:04.130 --> 01:52:06.598
And your own brothers will be...

01:52:07.700 --> 01:52:09.133
...jealous...

01:52:09.802 --> 01:52:11.531
...hostile.

01:52:12.472 --> 01:52:13.769
Go slowly.

01:52:14.073 --> 01:52:15.199
Yes, sir.

01:52:16.543 --> 01:52:17.976
Here's a glass.

01:52:24.784 --> 01:52:26.752
It's dirty water.

01:52:26.953 --> 01:52:28.045
Foul.

01:52:29.856 --> 01:52:32.290
If you offer this to the people...

01:52:32.492 --> 01:52:34.323
...they have no choice.

01:52:34.761 --> 01:52:36.228
They'll drink from it...

01:52:37.196 --> 01:52:38.754
...if they're thirsty.

01:52:39.699 --> 01:52:41.530
But if you offer them...

01:52:42.335 --> 01:52:44.030
...this glass...

01:52:46.839 --> 01:52:50.070
...and let them make
their own decision...

01:52:50.910 --> 01:52:54.175
...they will choose the pure vessel.

01:52:56.182 --> 01:52:57.649
Islam is...

01:52:58.084 --> 01:53:00.348
...the only religion...

01:53:01.521 --> 01:53:04.649
...that addresses
the needs and the problems...

01:53:04.857 --> 01:53:09.089
...of the so-called Negro in America.
Especially in the slums...

01:53:09.295 --> 01:53:10.694
...in the ghettos.

01:53:11.397 --> 01:53:15.493
Islam is the only way out
for drugs and crime...

01:53:15.702 --> 01:53:17.897
...and unemployment, prostitution...

01:53:18.104 --> 01:53:19.731
...alcohol...

01:53:19.939 --> 01:53:21.338
...gambling...

01:53:21.541 --> 01:53:23.805
...and adultery, fornication.

01:53:25.111 --> 01:53:26.203
<i>This sweet...</i>

01:53:26.446 --> 01:53:30.780
<i>...gentle man, at whose feet I kneeled,</i>
<i>gave me the truth from his own mouth.</i>

01:53:31.050 --> 01:53:32.244
Present the pure vessel.

01:53:32.452 --> 01:53:36.786
<i>I adored him in the sense of</i>
<i>the Latin root of the word</i> adorare...

01:53:36.990 --> 01:53:39.049
<i>...which means to worship and to fear.</i>

01:53:39.592 --> 01:53:41.423
<i>He was the first man I ever feared.</i>

01:53:41.628 --> 01:53:44.256
<i>I don't mean fear</i>
<i>such as one has of a gun...</i>

01:53:44.464 --> 01:53:48.264
<i>...but the fear one has</i>
<i>of the power of the sun.</i>

01:53:48.568 --> 01:53:51.867
<i>I pledged myself to him,</i>
<i>even if it cost me my life.</i>

01:53:55.341 --> 01:53:57.104
-<i>Hello?</i>
-Hello, Betty?

01:53:57.410 --> 01:53:58.638
Yeah, this is Malcolm.

01:53:59.045 --> 01:54:01.707
-I know.
-<i>Right, I'm here in Detroit.</i>

01:54:05.818 --> 01:54:07.945
-Will you marry me?
-Yes.

01:54:08.354 --> 01:54:09.787
<i>You heard what I said, right?</i>

01:54:09.989 --> 01:54:12.389
-<i>Did you hear my answer?</i>
-Yes, I think so.

01:54:14.927 --> 01:54:17.589
-<i>Are you eating?</i>
-I've been eating.

01:54:17.830 --> 01:54:18.888
<i>Good.</i>

01:54:19.632 --> 01:54:20.997
<i>I love you, Betty.</i>

01:54:23.603 --> 01:54:25.594
<i>I love you back.</i>

01:54:35.882 --> 01:54:37.281
It's not gonna be easy.

01:54:37.483 --> 01:54:39.007
No choice.

01:54:39.519 --> 01:54:41.111
I'll be away a lot.

01:54:41.954 --> 01:54:43.216
I know.

01:54:46.025 --> 01:54:47.993
In fact, I'm leaving in the morning.

01:54:48.194 --> 01:54:49.684
Hush, now.

01:54:50.530 --> 01:54:52.691
Pittsburgh, Philadelphia...

01:54:54.367 --> 01:54:58.133
...Trenton, Newark, up through number 7
all the way up to Boston.

01:55:04.911 --> 01:55:06.606
You're with me...

01:55:07.914 --> 01:55:09.882
...even when you're away.

01:55:26.399 --> 01:55:28.731
I've never told you this...

01:55:31.337 --> 01:55:34.170
...but the very first time
I ever saw you...

01:55:35.241 --> 01:55:37.334
...standing up on the podium...

01:55:39.946 --> 01:55:42.176
...you were cleaning your glasses...

01:55:44.851 --> 01:55:47.581
...and I felt so sorry for you.

01:55:48.521 --> 01:55:49.852
Sorry for me?

01:55:50.323 --> 01:55:51.187
Why?

01:55:51.390 --> 01:55:56.020
Because no one as young as you
should be so serious.

01:55:58.998 --> 01:56:01.023
But I don't think that anymore.

01:56:01.667 --> 01:56:03.032
What do you think?

01:56:06.038 --> 01:56:08.939
I want to have
a lot of babies with you.

01:56:12.712 --> 01:56:14.202
Dear heart.

01:56:16.783 --> 01:56:18.216
I love you.

01:56:20.453 --> 01:56:23.354
We're waiting on you folks.
Trying to starve us?

01:56:26.793 --> 01:56:28.920
Brother Malcolm, Sister Betty...

01:56:29.128 --> 01:56:33.656
...we pray that Allah blesses you
with a happy and fruitful marriage.

01:56:36.669 --> 01:56:39.001
Congratulations, Brother Minister.

01:56:41.307 --> 01:56:43.571
Check them out. Front page!

01:56:48.080 --> 01:56:52.949
I must emphasize at the start that
Elijah Muhammad is not a politician.

01:56:53.586 --> 01:56:58.421
So I'm not here this afternoon
as a Republican nor as a Democrat.

01:56:59.992 --> 01:57:02.654
Not as a Mason nor as an Elk.

01:57:03.996 --> 01:57:06.726
Not as a Protestant nor a Catholic.

01:57:06.933 --> 01:57:09.629
Not as a Christian nor a Jew.

01:57:09.836 --> 01:57:12.168
Not as a Baptist nor a Methodist.

01:57:12.371 --> 01:57:14.771
In fact, not even as an American.

01:57:15.508 --> 01:57:17.601
Because if I was an American...

01:57:17.844 --> 01:57:21.473
...the problem that confronts our people
today wouldn't even exist.

01:57:24.884 --> 01:57:28.320
So I have to stand here today
as what I was when I was born...

01:57:28.621 --> 01:57:30.179
...a black man.

01:57:34.794 --> 01:57:39.493
Before there was any such thing as a
Republican or a Democrat, we were black.

01:57:39.699 --> 01:57:43.499
Before there was any such thing
as a Mason or an Elk, we were black.

01:57:43.703 --> 01:57:47.935
Before there was any such thing as a Jew
or a Christian, we were black people.

01:57:48.140 --> 01:57:52.509
In fact, before there was any such place
as America, we were black.

01:57:52.778 --> 01:57:56.270
And after America has long passed
from the scene...

01:57:56.482 --> 01:57:58.950
...there will still be black people.

01:57:59.986 --> 01:58:02.648
I'm gonna tell you like it really is!

01:58:03.389 --> 01:58:08.190
Every election year, these politicians
are sent up here to pacify us.

01:58:08.394 --> 01:58:11.192
They're sent here and set up here
by the white man.

01:58:11.397 --> 01:58:12.694
This is what they do.

01:58:12.899 --> 01:58:15.800
They send drugs in Harlem down here
to pacify us!

01:58:16.002 --> 01:58:18.698
They send alcohol down here
to pacify us!

01:58:18.905 --> 01:58:21.874
They send prostitution down here
to pacify us!

01:58:22.074 --> 01:58:25.475
You can't get drugs in Harlem
without the white man's permission.

01:58:25.678 --> 01:58:28.977
You can't get prostitution in Harlem
without the white man's permission.

01:58:29.181 --> 01:58:32.344
You can't get gambling in Harlem
without the white man's permission.

01:58:32.551 --> 01:58:35.384
Every time you break the seal
on that liquor bottle...

01:58:35.588 --> 01:58:38.148
...that's a government seal
you're breaking.

01:58:38.357 --> 01:58:42.225
I say, and I say it again,
you been had.

01:58:42.428 --> 01:58:43.952
You been took.

01:58:44.163 --> 01:58:45.755
You been hoodwinked.

01:58:46.098 --> 01:58:48.692
Bamboozled. Led astray.

01:58:48.935 --> 01:58:51.426
Run amuck. This is what he does.

01:58:51.704 --> 01:58:54.400
You know, some people
call this hate-teaching.

01:58:54.740 --> 01:58:56.708
This isn't hate-teaching.

01:58:56.909 --> 01:58:58.536
This is love-teaching.

01:58:59.145 --> 01:59:01.670
I wouldn't tell you this
if I didn't love you.

01:59:01.881 --> 01:59:04.679
I wouldn't stick my neck out for you
if I didn't love you.

01:59:04.884 --> 01:59:07.751
I want you to understand one thing:
Everything I teach you...

01:59:07.954 --> 01:59:10.013
...everything I have said to you...

01:59:10.222 --> 01:59:13.214
...has been taught to me
by this dear man.

01:59:13.459 --> 01:59:14.721
This divine man.

01:59:16.295 --> 01:59:19.787
All praise is due to Allah
for the Honorable Elijah Muhammad.

01:59:20.466 --> 01:59:22.297
<i>Attallah's fine.</i>

01:59:22.501 --> 01:59:25.061
<i>And she misses you as much as I do.</i>

01:59:25.471 --> 01:59:29.703
<i>But the news that you've dedicated</i>
<i>four new temples is almost as good...</i>

01:59:29.909 --> 01:59:33.276
<i>...as having you with us.</i>
<i>Oh, dear heart.</i>

01:59:33.479 --> 01:59:38.280
--<i>white supremacy, try to hide their</i>
<i>guilt by accusing Elijah Muhammad...</i>

01:59:38.484 --> 01:59:40.111
<i>...of being a black supremacist...</i>

01:59:40.319 --> 01:59:43.117
<i>...simply because he's trying</i>
<i>to uplift the mentality...</i>

01:59:43.322 --> 01:59:46.155
<i>...the social and economic condition</i>
<i>of his people.</i>

01:59:46.359 --> 01:59:50.455
<i>And the Jews who have been guilty</i>
<i>of exploiting black people...</i>

01:59:50.663 --> 01:59:53.928
<i>...try to hide their guilt</i>
<i>by accusing Elijah Muhammad...</i>

01:59:54.166 --> 01:59:56.225
<i>...of being anti-Semitic...</i>

01:59:56.435 --> 01:59:59.836
...simply because he's trying
to teach you and l--

02:00:00.039 --> 02:00:02.030
<i>He's trying to teach you and I...</i>

02:00:02.241 --> 02:00:05.404
<i>...to be in charge of the businesses</i>
<i>in our own community.</i>

02:00:05.611 --> 02:00:08.307
<i>To own the businesses</i>
<i>in our own community.</i>

02:00:08.514 --> 02:00:11.176
<i>To have economic leadership</i>
<i>in our own community.</i>

02:00:12.084 --> 02:00:13.984
<i>No, this isn't black supremacy...</i>

02:00:14.186 --> 02:00:16.552
<i>...this is black intelligence.</i>

02:00:33.439 --> 02:00:35.737
<i>The black people in this country...</i>

02:00:36.142 --> 02:00:38.542
<i>...have been the victims</i>
<i>of violence...</i>

02:00:39.045 --> 02:00:41.639
<i>...at the hands</i>
<i>of the American right wing...</i>

02:00:41.847 --> 02:00:44.975
<i>...for 400 years.</i>

02:00:45.384 --> 02:00:47.477
<i>Four hundred years.</i>

02:00:48.054 --> 02:00:49.817
<i>Four hundred years.</i>

02:00:52.124 --> 02:00:55.218
<i>We thought by following</i>
<i>those ignorant Negro preachers...</i>

02:00:55.428 --> 02:00:57.896
<i>...that it was God-like</i>
<i>to turn the other cheek...</i>

02:00:58.097 --> 02:01:00.588
<i>...to the group</i>
<i>that was brutalizing us.</i>

02:01:01.000 --> 02:01:04.697
A hundred years ago,
they used to put on white sheets...

02:01:04.904 --> 02:01:07.031
...and sic bloodhounds on us.

02:01:07.239 --> 02:01:09.639
Nowadays, they've traded in
the sheets--

02:01:09.842 --> 02:01:11.571
Some have traded in the sheets--

02:01:12.912 --> 02:01:14.971
<i>They've traded in the sheets</i>--

02:01:15.181 --> 02:01:16.546
<i>Please, please.</i>

02:01:16.749 --> 02:01:20.082
<i>They've traded in those white sheets</i>
<i>for police uniforms.</i>

02:01:20.419 --> 02:01:23.513
<i>They traded in the bloodhounds</i>
<i>for police dogs.</i>

02:01:23.722 --> 02:01:26.384
<i>And just like Uncle Tom</i>
<i>back during slavery time....</i>

02:01:26.592 --> 02:01:31.086
<i>We must remain true to nonviolence.</i>
<i>I'm asking everybody in the line.</i>

02:01:31.430 --> 02:01:34.024
<i>If you can't be nonviolent,</i>
<i>don't get in it.</i>

02:01:34.233 --> 02:01:37.225
--To love our enemy and pray
for those who use us spitefully.

02:01:37.436 --> 02:01:41.600
You've got chicken-pecking Uncle Tom,
so-called Negro leaders today.

02:01:41.807 --> 02:01:43.900
<i>And it's another great day.</i>

02:01:44.110 --> 02:01:47.876
<i>You've got these Uncle Tom</i>
<i>Negro leaders today...</i>

02:01:48.080 --> 02:01:50.674
<i>...that tell us we ought to pray</i>
<i>for our enemies.</i>

02:01:50.883 --> 02:01:53.943
<i>We ought to love our enemy</i>
<i>and integrate with the enemy...</i>

02:01:54.153 --> 02:01:57.748
<i>...who bombs us, who kills</i>
<i>and shoots us, who lynches us...</i>

02:01:57.957 --> 02:02:00.858
<i>...who rapes our women</i>
<i>and children. No!</i>

02:02:03.229 --> 02:02:05.288
<i>No! That's not intelligent.</i>

02:02:05.564 --> 02:02:07.361
<i>That's not intelligent.</i>

02:02:07.566 --> 02:02:10.262
Elijah Muhammad is trying
to teach you and I...

02:02:10.469 --> 02:02:13.802
...that just as the white man
and any other man on this earth...

02:02:14.006 --> 02:02:17.442
...has the God-given right,
the human right, the civil right...

02:02:17.643 --> 02:02:20.578
...the natural right, and any other
rights you can think of...

02:02:20.813 --> 02:02:22.542
...to protect himself...

02:02:22.748 --> 02:02:26.309
...just as this white man has
the right to defend himself...

02:02:26.585 --> 02:02:29.315
...we have the right
to defend ourselves too.

02:02:29.889 --> 02:02:34.258
This is only natural. This is what
Elijah Muhammad is trying to teach.

02:02:34.460 --> 02:02:36.451
He's not teaching us
to hate the white man.

02:02:36.662 --> 02:02:39.153
He's teaching us to love ourselves.

02:02:40.332 --> 02:02:44.359
<i>Mr. X, before we begin</i>
<i>our discussion tonight...</i>

02:02:44.570 --> 02:02:47.903
<i>... "The Black Muslims: Hate Mongers"...</i>

02:02:48.607 --> 02:02:52.168
<i>...would you mind explaining for us</i>
<i>the meaning of your name...</i>

02:02:52.378 --> 02:02:54.812
<i>...which is the letter "X"?</i>

02:02:55.447 --> 02:02:58.314
During slavery time,
the slave master...

02:02:58.517 --> 02:03:01.042
...gave the Negro--
the so-called Negro...

02:03:01.253 --> 02:03:04.416
...named the so-called Negro
after themselves.

02:03:05.524 --> 02:03:07.253
Elijah Muhammad teaches us...

02:03:07.459 --> 02:03:11.156
...that once we come into the knowledge
of Islam, the knowledge of ourselves...

02:03:11.363 --> 02:03:13.991
...we replace our slave name
with an "X" ...

02:03:14.200 --> 02:03:17.101
..."X" in mathematics representing
the unknown.

02:03:17.369 --> 02:03:20.463
Since we've been disconnected,
or cut off from our own history...

02:03:20.673 --> 02:03:23.642
...our own past, our own culture,
our own land...

02:03:23.842 --> 02:03:27.573
...we use the "X," the unknown,
until we get back to our country.

02:03:27.780 --> 02:03:31.045
I see. Thank you. Dr. Payson?

02:03:31.250 --> 02:03:33.912
Mr. X is a....
He's a demagogue.

02:03:34.119 --> 02:03:36.883
He has no place to go,
so he exaggerates.

02:03:37.122 --> 02:03:38.350
He's a disservice to...

02:03:38.557 --> 02:03:42.391
...every good, law-abiding, church-going
American Negro in the country.

02:03:46.465 --> 02:03:49.593
Why do you teach black supremacy?

02:03:49.802 --> 02:03:51.736
Why do you teach hate?

02:03:51.937 --> 02:03:54.405
Well, for the white man...

02:03:54.607 --> 02:03:57.075
...to ask the black man...

02:03:57.576 --> 02:03:59.009
...why he hates him...

02:03:59.245 --> 02:04:03.147
...is like the wolf asking the sheep,
or the rapist asking the raped...

02:04:03.349 --> 02:04:04.373
..."Do you hate me?"

02:04:04.583 --> 02:04:08.212
The white man is in no moral position
to accuse the black man of anything.

02:04:08.420 --> 02:04:10.388
<i>This is a black man</i>
<i>asking the question.</i>

02:04:10.589 --> 02:04:14.753
<i>What would you call an educated Negro</i>
<i>with a B.A., an M.A., a B.S. Or a Ph.D.?</i>

02:04:14.960 --> 02:04:18.418
You call him a nigger.
That's what the white man calls him.

02:04:18.631 --> 02:04:20.826
You have to understand this thinking.

02:04:21.033 --> 02:04:24.662
To understand this type of man,
you must understand that historically...

02:04:24.870 --> 02:04:28.533
...there were two types of slaves:
The house Negro and the field Negro.

02:04:28.741 --> 02:04:30.538
The house Negro lived in the house...

02:04:30.743 --> 02:04:34.406
...next to his master. In the big house,
in the basement or the attic.

02:04:34.647 --> 02:04:37.377
He dressed good, he ate good,
what the master left him.

02:04:37.583 --> 02:04:39.210
He loved his master.

02:04:39.418 --> 02:04:42.615
He loved his master better
than the master loved himself.

02:04:42.821 --> 02:04:47.121
If master said, "We got a nice house,"
you say, "Yeah, we got a nice house."

02:04:47.493 --> 02:04:49.859
Master's house caught on fire,
the house Negro...

02:04:50.329 --> 02:04:51.591
...would put the blaze out.

02:04:51.797 --> 02:04:55.130
If the master got sick, he'd say,
"What's the matter? We sick?"

02:04:55.534 --> 02:04:58.196
"We sick" ! This is the thinking
of the house Negro.

02:04:58.404 --> 02:05:00.133
If another slave said...

02:05:00.339 --> 02:05:03.206
..."Let's run away, let's separate
from this cruel master" ...

02:05:03.409 --> 02:05:06.344
...he said, "Why? What's better
than what we got here?

02:05:06.545 --> 02:05:08.979
I'm not going anywhere."
This is the house Negro.

02:05:09.181 --> 02:05:11.012
In those days, we called them
house niggers.

02:05:11.216 --> 02:05:15.277
That's what we call them today because
we still got a lot of house niggers.

02:05:16.221 --> 02:05:17.381
Dear Holy Apostle...

02:05:19.224 --> 02:05:22.489
...the ministers think Malcolm is
getting too much press.

02:05:23.796 --> 02:05:26.424
They think he thinks he is
the Nation of Islam.

02:05:28.300 --> 02:05:30.962
That he has aspirations
to lead the Nation.

02:05:32.037 --> 02:05:34.938
It was you who made Malcolm
the man he is.

02:05:35.140 --> 02:05:36.630
You lifted him out of darkness.

02:05:40.245 --> 02:05:42.873
You go and tell the brothers...

02:05:43.615 --> 02:05:45.344
...that what the Brother Minister...

02:05:45.718 --> 02:05:47.583
...is doing, has done...

02:05:47.886 --> 02:05:52.289
...has been of great benefit
to the Nation.

02:05:52.491 --> 02:05:54.482
And you tell them that I say so.

02:05:54.693 --> 02:05:57.321
The ministers think he is
of great benefit to himself.

02:06:07.106 --> 02:06:07.970
One at a time.

02:06:08.173 --> 02:06:11.233
-<i>Did you say white people are devils?</i>
-<i>I said they're devils.</i>

02:06:11.443 --> 02:06:13.206
<i>Should all black men be armed?</i>

02:06:13.412 --> 02:06:15.778
Well, one of your most
famous men said:

02:06:15.981 --> 02:06:19.508
"Praise the Lord and pass the
ammunition." That's the way you think.

02:06:19.718 --> 02:06:22.050
<i>Do you think your cause</i>
<i>will be successful?</i>

02:06:22.254 --> 02:06:23.585
<i>I sincerely hope so.</i>

02:06:23.789 --> 02:06:26.087
-Do you advocate violence?
-No, sir.

02:06:26.291 --> 02:06:28.486
Has a white man helped your people?

02:06:28.694 --> 02:06:31.254
<i>Has there been a white man</i>
<i>that's helped my people?</i>

02:06:31.463 --> 02:06:33.658
-<i>Correct.</i>
-<i>I don't understand the question.</i>

02:06:33.866 --> 02:06:36.027
<i>You preach anti-white,</i>
<i>anti-Christian science.</i>

02:06:36.235 --> 02:06:38.135
You're saying you're anti-white?

02:06:38.337 --> 02:06:41.306
-No, you're saying it.
-Are all white people devils?

02:06:41.940 --> 02:06:45.398
<i>We've gotta move out.</i>
<i>We've got a plane to catch.</i>

02:06:47.980 --> 02:06:50.312
Excuse me, Mr. X?

02:06:51.016 --> 02:06:52.916
I've read some of your speeches...

02:06:53.118 --> 02:06:56.849
...and I honestly believe that a lot
of what you have to say is true.

02:06:57.055 --> 02:07:00.115
I'm a good person in spite
of what my ancestors did.

02:07:00.325 --> 02:07:02.384
I just wanted to ask you...

02:07:02.594 --> 02:07:05.461
...what can a white person
like me, who isn't prejudiced...

02:07:05.664 --> 02:07:09.225
...what can I do to help you
and further your cause?

02:07:09.435 --> 02:07:10.527
Nothing.

02:07:18.076 --> 02:07:20.476
<i>My high school was a black ghetto...</i>

02:07:20.679 --> 02:07:22.840
<i>...in Roxbury, right here in Boston.</i>

02:07:23.682 --> 02:07:27.277
<i>I got my college education on</i>
<i>the streets of Harlem in New York City.</i>

02:07:28.120 --> 02:07:30.645
I took my master's degree in prison...

02:07:31.089 --> 02:07:32.647
...over six and a half years.

02:07:32.858 --> 02:07:34.086
In fact...

02:07:34.293 --> 02:07:37.956
...my old burglary hangout
was just outside this campus.

02:07:38.730 --> 02:07:40.197
I lived like an animal.

02:07:41.133 --> 02:07:42.532
I stole.

02:07:42.868 --> 02:07:44.665
I used drugs.

02:07:45.671 --> 02:07:48.697
I smoked reefers, cocaine.

02:07:48.907 --> 02:07:52.707
I committed adultery. Had it not been
for the Honorable Elijah Muhammad...

02:07:53.479 --> 02:07:56.312
...l'd have surely been in
an insane asylum or dead...

02:07:56.515 --> 02:07:59.245
...or possibly even a murderer
of one of you.

02:07:59.451 --> 02:08:03.683
So what is Mr. Muhammad trying to do?
He's trying to get us on God's side...

02:08:03.922 --> 02:08:07.585
...so that God will be on our side
and help us fight our battles.

02:08:07.793 --> 02:08:10.626
When the so-called Negro in America
gets on God's side...

02:08:10.829 --> 02:08:13.423
...and listens to the teachings
of Elijah Muhammad...

02:08:13.632 --> 02:08:17.068
...he'll want to get off of drugs
and get away from a life of crime.

02:08:17.269 --> 02:08:19.931
He'll want to get away
from committing adultery.

02:08:20.138 --> 02:08:23.039
Then he'd want to get off welfare.
He'd want a job...

02:08:23.242 --> 02:08:26.803
...to take care of his family.
And his family would respect him.

02:08:27.012 --> 02:08:29.480
His son will say,
"I'm proud that that's my father."

02:08:29.681 --> 02:08:32.411
His wife will say,
"I'm proud that that's my husband."

02:08:32.618 --> 02:08:37.248
"Father" only means that you take care
of your children. That's what it is.

02:08:37.456 --> 02:08:40.448
"Father" doesn't mean
that you're having some babies.

02:08:40.659 --> 02:08:42.217
That doesn't make you a father.

02:08:42.427 --> 02:08:44.190
Anybody can go out and get a woman.

02:08:44.396 --> 02:08:47.365
But not anybody can take care
of that woman.

02:08:47.566 --> 02:08:50.296
There's another word for it.
It's called responsibility.

02:08:50.869 --> 02:08:55.329
If the so-called Negro in America
was truly an American citizen...

02:08:55.541 --> 02:08:57.509
...we wouldn't have a racial problem.

02:08:57.709 --> 02:09:00.769
If the Emancipation Proclamation
was authentic...

02:09:01.313 --> 02:09:03.611
...if the 13th, 14th and 15th
amendments...

02:09:03.815 --> 02:09:06.545
...were authentic,
we wouldn't have a race problem.

02:09:06.785 --> 02:09:09.754
If the Supreme Court desegregation
decision were authentic...

02:09:09.955 --> 02:09:11.445
...we wouldn't have a race problem.

02:09:12.190 --> 02:09:15.182
But you have to see
that all of this is hypocrisy.

02:09:15.394 --> 02:09:18.124
These Negro leaders are telling
the white man...

02:09:18.330 --> 02:09:21.163
...that everything's all right,
we got it under control.

02:09:21.366 --> 02:09:24.028
That everything Elijah Muhammad
teaches is wrong.

02:09:24.236 --> 02:09:27.728
Mr. Muhammad said these things
were gonna come to pass...

02:09:27.940 --> 02:09:29.805
...and now they're coming to pass.

02:09:32.611 --> 02:09:35.307
Now these same Negro leaders...

02:09:36.448 --> 02:09:41.078
...are running around talking about
there's about to be a racial explosion.

02:09:42.988 --> 02:09:45.582
Yes, there's gonna be
a racial explosion.

02:09:46.058 --> 02:09:50.586
And a racial explosion is
more dangerous than an atomic explosion.

02:09:52.264 --> 02:09:56.394
There's going to be an explosion because
black people are dissatisfied...

02:09:56.602 --> 02:10:00.800
...not only with the white man, but with
these Uncle Tom Negro leaders...

02:10:01.006 --> 02:10:02.871
...that try to pose
as spokesmen...

02:10:03.075 --> 02:10:04.542
...for you and I.

02:10:04.977 --> 02:10:06.171
Just like you have a--

02:10:06.979 --> 02:10:08.708
Just like you have a powder keg.

02:10:09.047 --> 02:10:11.607
When you have a powder keg
and there's too many sparks...

02:10:11.817 --> 02:10:13.444
...the thing's going to explode.

02:10:13.652 --> 02:10:17.418
If the thing that's going to explode
is sitting inside the house...

02:10:17.623 --> 02:10:20.615
...and if it explodes, then the house
is going to be destroyed.

02:10:20.826 --> 02:10:23.659
I said the house is going
to be destroyed.

02:10:23.862 --> 02:10:26.422
The Honorable Elijah Muhammad is
teaching you and I...

02:10:26.632 --> 02:10:30.591
...and trying to tell the white man
to get this powder keg out of his house.

02:10:30.936 --> 02:10:33.268
Let the black man separate
from his house.

02:10:33.505 --> 02:10:35.473
Let the black man have his own house.

02:10:35.674 --> 02:10:38.438
Let the black man have
his own land and property.

02:10:41.346 --> 02:10:44.338
The Honorable Elijah Muhammad is
trying to tell the white man...

02:10:44.549 --> 02:10:48.485
...that this thing, this explosion, is
gonna bring down his house.

02:10:48.687 --> 02:10:52.145
This is what he's telling him.
More importantly, he's telling him...

02:10:52.357 --> 02:10:54.348
...that if he doesn't do
something about it...

02:10:54.559 --> 02:10:59.496
...if he doesn't do something about it,
it's gonna explode any day now.

02:10:59.831 --> 02:11:03.096
I'm just here to tell you,
and I'm gonna make it very short.

02:11:03.635 --> 02:11:07.571
I'm here to tell you about
Elijah Muhammad's greatest greatness.

02:11:07.906 --> 02:11:11.137
His greatest greatness is
that he has the only solution...

02:11:11.343 --> 02:11:13.402
...for peace in this country.

02:11:13.845 --> 02:11:16.336
The Honorable Elijah Muhammad's
solution...

02:11:16.548 --> 02:11:18.675
...is the only solution for you and I.

02:11:18.884 --> 02:11:21.512
It's the only solution
for the white man.

02:11:22.754 --> 02:11:25.188
Complete separation...

02:11:25.524 --> 02:11:29.016
...between the black race
and the white race.

02:11:31.630 --> 02:11:33.495
It's the only solution.

02:11:39.871 --> 02:11:42.101
All praise due to Allah
for Elijah Muhammad!

02:11:42.307 --> 02:11:44.639
All praise due to Allah
for Elijah Muhammad!

02:12:20.479 --> 02:12:22.242
Brother Malcolm!

02:12:23.081 --> 02:12:25.811
Yes, yes. Hold on, hold on.

02:12:26.651 --> 02:12:29.950
Yes, sir. It's all right.
My brother. How you doing?

02:12:30.155 --> 02:12:32.214
-Can I ask you something?
-Anything.

02:12:32.424 --> 02:12:34.221
Are you Elijah's pimp?

02:12:34.426 --> 02:12:37.088
He should be killed
for talking like that!

02:12:38.330 --> 02:12:39.922
What are you saying, brother?

02:12:40.432 --> 02:12:42.059
"His greatest greatness."

02:12:42.267 --> 02:12:44.030
Just say what you're saying.

02:12:45.837 --> 02:12:47.532
If you don't know...

02:12:47.873 --> 02:12:49.272
...I feel the sorriest for you.

02:12:49.474 --> 02:12:51.499
Oh, come on, brother.

02:12:52.677 --> 02:12:54.440
Let me tell you something.

02:13:03.555 --> 02:13:04.852
It's all right.

02:13:08.960 --> 02:13:11.485
He's just hungry for knowledge,
that's all.

02:13:11.696 --> 02:13:13.857
Yeah, that brother's starving.

02:13:14.199 --> 02:13:16.861
So am I. Come on,
let's get something to eat.

02:13:18.470 --> 02:13:20.097
We'll talk about it tomorrow.

02:13:20.305 --> 02:13:22.830
-Okay, night-night, Daddy.
-Night-night.

02:13:38.390 --> 02:13:39.584
Long night.

02:13:46.798 --> 02:13:48.595
-What you looking at?
-You.

02:13:48.800 --> 02:13:50.267
Why you looking like that?

02:13:50.468 --> 02:13:51.730
You're in trouble.

02:13:53.972 --> 02:13:54.961
How do you know?

02:13:55.173 --> 02:13:57.232
Oh, dear heart.

02:13:57.876 --> 02:13:59.173
Because I know you.

02:13:59.377 --> 02:14:01.072
Well, if you know me...

02:14:02.914 --> 02:14:05.781
...you know I don't like to bring
my troubles home.

02:14:07.419 --> 02:14:08.909
You know that also.

02:14:11.756 --> 02:14:12.916
Yes, I do.

02:14:15.393 --> 02:14:17.452
But I'm not made of glass.

02:14:17.662 --> 02:14:19.653
And I won't break.

02:14:27.138 --> 02:14:29.368
Look, Betty, I just want peace.

02:14:30.909 --> 02:14:33.173
I want to sit here with you.
I want to...

02:14:34.479 --> 02:14:37.539
...be still. I want peace in my house.

02:14:41.219 --> 02:14:43.949
-Have we ever had a fight?
-Never.

02:14:44.155 --> 02:14:46.521
-Argument?
-Never had one, no.

02:14:49.361 --> 02:14:51.022
We're gonna have one...

02:14:52.330 --> 02:14:55.026
-...if you don't talk about it.
-Talk about what?

02:14:55.233 --> 02:14:59.431
-The talk's everywhere.
-There's always gonna be talk.

02:14:59.638 --> 02:15:02.971
Aren't they talking now about me trying
to take over the Nation?

02:15:03.241 --> 02:15:06.301
Aren't they talking about
how we're getting rich...

02:15:06.511 --> 02:15:08.342
...off the Nation of Islam?

02:15:08.546 --> 02:15:11.310
-We could talk about that too.
-Let's talk about it.

02:15:11.716 --> 02:15:13.513
It's not just talk anymore.

02:15:13.718 --> 02:15:17.119
"UPl: Elijah Muhammad, 67...

02:15:17.322 --> 02:15:20.086
...leader of
the Black Muslim movement...

02:15:20.292 --> 02:15:24.626
...today faced paternity suits
from two former secretaries."

02:15:24.829 --> 02:15:28.230
These are slanders. These are lies.
Don't you know that?

02:15:28.433 --> 02:15:32.494
Don't you realize this is
the devil's newspaper?

02:15:32.837 --> 02:15:34.896
He's trying to divide us.

02:15:35.407 --> 02:15:39.571
Divide and conquer. He's trying
to bring down our leader.

02:15:43.014 --> 02:15:44.345
"Both women...

02:15:45.183 --> 02:15:48.812
...in their 20s, charge that
they had intimacy--"

02:15:49.020 --> 02:15:51.887
"Intimacies with Mr. Muhammad--"

02:16:00.165 --> 02:16:04.158
You think I'm not
aware of these accusations?

02:16:04.369 --> 02:16:07.702
You think I'm not
aware of these vicious lies?

02:16:09.808 --> 02:16:13.039
-Brother Baines and I discussed it today.
-Baines?

02:16:13.645 --> 02:16:14.839
Is he your friend?

02:16:15.080 --> 02:16:15.910
What's wrong?

02:16:16.114 --> 02:16:18.582
Nothing.
What's the matter with you?

02:16:18.783 --> 02:16:22.344
Wake up! Are you so committed that
you've blinded yourself?

02:16:22.554 --> 02:16:25.352
You're so dedicated,
you can't face the truth?

02:16:25.557 --> 02:16:26.819
Baines?

02:16:27.058 --> 02:16:30.494
He's the editor of the newspaper
that you established.

02:16:30.729 --> 02:16:35.029
Ask him why your name hasn't
appeared in it for over a year.

02:16:35.233 --> 02:16:38.861
-I'm not interested in publicity.
-You're in every other paper.

02:16:39.070 --> 02:16:42.300
Our people know what I'm doing.

02:16:42.507 --> 02:16:45.532
-But do you know what Baines is doing?
-Baines! Baines!

02:16:45.744 --> 02:16:49.736
You're so blind!
Everyone can see but you!

02:16:51.415 --> 02:16:54.852
Baines is the one who saved my life.

02:16:55.053 --> 02:16:57.351
When I crawled in prison
like an animal...

02:16:57.555 --> 02:17:00.183
...he brought me to
the Honorable Elijah Muhammad.

02:17:00.392 --> 02:17:02.986
And Mr. Muhammad brought me
back from the dead--

02:17:03.193 --> 02:17:05.218
A long time ago!
You've repaid them!

02:17:05.430 --> 02:17:08.126
Don't you raise your voice
in my house!

02:17:12.603 --> 02:17:14.093
Ask them.

02:17:15.607 --> 02:17:18.405
Ask them why they have new cars,
houses and furniture.

02:17:18.610 --> 02:17:21.170
Is that what this is about?
You want furniture?

02:17:21.379 --> 02:17:23.677
-You want cars?
-What do we have?

02:17:23.882 --> 02:17:25.873
What do we have, Malcolm?

02:17:26.217 --> 02:17:28.208
Broken-down jalopy....

02:17:29.320 --> 02:17:31.254
The clothes on our backs.

02:17:31.589 --> 02:17:33.317
So I'll get you new clothes....

02:17:33.525 --> 02:17:36.016
We don't even own our own home.

02:17:36.227 --> 02:17:39.162
What about our children?
What about me?

02:17:39.531 --> 02:17:41.522
We don't even own life insurance.

02:17:41.733 --> 02:17:45.100
The Nation will support all of you
if anything happens to me--

02:17:45.303 --> 02:17:46.291
Will they?

02:17:47.472 --> 02:17:48.734
Are you sure?

02:17:50.308 --> 02:17:51.638
Are you sure?

02:17:52.644 --> 02:17:53.975
Are you sure?

02:17:55.647 --> 02:17:57.308
Or are you blind?

02:18:00.818 --> 02:18:01.808
All right.

02:18:07.759 --> 02:18:09.659
I've got work to do, so....

02:18:11.329 --> 02:18:13.320
There's always work to do.

02:18:13.598 --> 02:18:15.395
-Help me.
-I'm trying to.

02:18:15.600 --> 02:18:19.127
I'm raising the children
practically by myself.

02:18:19.337 --> 02:18:21.965
What do you want me to do?
Stay home?

02:18:22.173 --> 02:18:25.609
You don't know how often they ask,
"Where's Daddy?"

02:18:25.809 --> 02:18:28.472
You want me to make the beds
and go on the road?

02:18:28.680 --> 02:18:30.409
-The people need me!
-We need you!

02:18:30.615 --> 02:18:33.311
I need you too.
But what do you want me to do?

02:18:33.518 --> 02:18:35.611
Open your eyes. Open your eyes.

02:18:36.487 --> 02:18:40.822
You can face death 24 hours a day,
but the possibility of betrayal...

02:18:41.058 --> 02:18:43.186
...never enters your head.

02:18:46.464 --> 02:18:48.364
Open your eyes.

02:19:24.936 --> 02:19:27.837
-As-Salaam-Alaikum, minister
-Alaikum-Salaam, sister.

02:19:28.039 --> 02:19:30.007
Her name's Eva Marie.

02:19:31.009 --> 02:19:32.601
And she's 2 years old.

02:19:34.179 --> 02:19:36.942
Brother Minister,
I didn't do anything wrong.

02:19:37.182 --> 02:19:40.276
I didn't do anything to be
put in isolation.

02:19:41.451 --> 02:19:43.282
I believed in him.

02:19:44.689 --> 02:19:48.125
I believed in
the Honorable Elijah Muhammad.

02:19:49.794 --> 02:19:51.352
Believe in Allah.

02:19:55.967 --> 02:19:58.197
This is Saudi.
She's 2.

02:19:58.536 --> 02:20:00.504
And you have Lisha.
She's 3.

02:20:00.705 --> 02:20:05.438
<i>From their own mouths I heard</i>
<i>who had fathered their children.</i>

02:20:05.977 --> 02:20:08.878
<i>And from their own mouths</i>
<i>I heard that Mr. Muhammad...</i>

02:20:09.080 --> 02:20:11.207
<i>...had told them I was the best.</i>

02:20:11.983 --> 02:20:14.543
He often spoke of you.
He loves you like a son.

02:20:14.819 --> 02:20:17.947
<i>The greatest minister he had,</i>
<i>but that I would leave him...</i>

02:20:18.156 --> 02:20:21.421
<i>...turn against him.</i>
<i>And so I was dangerous.</i>

02:20:21.626 --> 02:20:25.392
<i>Mr. Muhammad, while praising me</i>
<i>to my face...</i>

02:20:26.130 --> 02:20:28.394
<i>...was tearing me apart</i>
<i>behind by back.</i>

02:20:28.666 --> 02:20:30.964
-You're sure about all this?
-Yes, I am.

02:20:31.202 --> 02:20:33.898
All I want is support for
my three children...

02:20:34.339 --> 02:20:37.399
...that the Honorable Elijah Muhammad
provide for them.

02:20:37.742 --> 02:20:39.471
That's all I want.

02:20:41.946 --> 02:20:43.971
Allah will provide...

02:20:47.652 --> 02:20:48.676
...for all of us.

02:20:48.920 --> 02:20:50.854
What do you mean, blackout?

02:20:51.055 --> 02:20:53.421
Perhaps some brothers are
a little jealous.

02:20:54.192 --> 02:20:57.389
Maybe they think you've been
getting too much press.

02:20:57.595 --> 02:20:59.222
It's nothing. Forget it.

02:20:59.430 --> 02:21:01.990
Now about our coming
up in the world a little.

02:21:02.200 --> 02:21:05.192
The Nation's grown.
We've grown with it.

02:21:06.170 --> 02:21:07.694
You know our people.

02:21:09.207 --> 02:21:11.505
They want their leaders
to be prosperous.

02:21:12.610 --> 02:21:14.407
One hand washes the other.

02:21:15.013 --> 02:21:18.210
"I'm telling you God's words,
not no hustle."

02:21:20.685 --> 02:21:22.744
Remember what you told me in prison?

02:21:22.954 --> 02:21:26.788
"I'm telling you God's words,
not no hustle."

02:21:28.726 --> 02:21:29.954
Brother Malcolm...

02:21:32.997 --> 02:21:35.363
...what do you want?
A new car?

02:21:35.967 --> 02:21:37.400
A new house?

02:21:38.936 --> 02:21:40.563
It's the money, isn't it?

02:21:45.643 --> 02:21:49.545
But we tell the whole world that
we're moral leaders...

02:21:49.881 --> 02:21:51.644
...because we follow...

02:21:52.317 --> 02:21:54.911
...the personal example of
Mr. Muhammad.

02:21:55.119 --> 02:21:57.246
Elijah Muhammad is a human being...

02:21:58.156 --> 02:21:59.418
...and so are you.

02:22:00.358 --> 02:22:02.121
-Do you know your Bible?
-Do you?

02:22:02.493 --> 02:22:04.427
David slept with Bathsheba...

02:22:04.629 --> 02:22:06.995
...but he's remembered for
slaying Goliath.

02:22:08.666 --> 02:22:12.659
Noah was accused of drunkenness,
but God gave him the ark.

02:22:13.971 --> 02:22:18.635
Solomon had 700 wives, but he
was history's greatest, wisest king.

02:22:18.843 --> 02:22:22.574
Brother Baines is a two-bit hustler,
but one hand washes the other.

02:22:22.780 --> 02:22:25.715
A great man's deeds
outweigh his personal weaknesses.

02:22:25.917 --> 02:22:28.249
Who needs the nutmeg now, brother?

02:22:28.453 --> 02:22:30.978
-I'm not gonna allow--
-Be careful, Malcolm.

02:22:32.957 --> 02:22:34.356
I warn you.

02:22:35.360 --> 02:22:36.588
You be careful.

02:23:05.957 --> 02:23:08.016
I'm not surprised.

02:23:11.195 --> 02:23:16.098
You have a very good understanding of
prophecy, of spiritual matters.

02:23:16.300 --> 02:23:18.359
I'm not surprised.

02:23:18.970 --> 02:23:21.666
I have built this Nation...

02:23:21.873 --> 02:23:25.172
...under the divine guidance of Allah.

02:23:25.977 --> 02:23:29.913
He has brought me back
from the dead to lead my people.

02:23:30.114 --> 02:23:32.514
After me,
there will be no more.

02:23:32.717 --> 02:23:34.480
No more.

02:23:38.489 --> 02:23:40.320
I must...

02:23:42.326 --> 02:23:45.591
...plant my seed in fertile soil.

02:23:45.830 --> 02:23:47.263
It is only...

02:23:47.932 --> 02:23:50.924
...the fulfillment of prophecy.

02:23:51.335 --> 02:23:55.169
<i>My faith had been shattered</i>
<i>in a way I can never fully describe.</i>

02:23:55.406 --> 02:23:58.170
<i>Every second of my 12 years</i>
<i>with Mr. Muhammad...</i>

02:23:58.376 --> 02:24:00.867
<i>...I'd been ready to die for him.</i>

02:24:01.078 --> 02:24:04.707
<i>The thing to me that is worse than</i>
<i>death itself is betrayal.</i>

02:24:04.916 --> 02:24:08.818
<i>I could conceive death,</i>
<i>but I couldn't conceive betrayal.</i>

02:24:09.020 --> 02:24:13.423
<i>Not of the loyalty I gave to</i>
<i>the Nation of Islam and Mr. Muhammad.</i>

02:24:13.691 --> 02:24:16.990
<i>During that time, if Mr. Muhammad</i>
<i>had committed any crime...</i>

02:24:17.195 --> 02:24:21.063
<i>...punishable by death, I would</i>
<i>have tried to prove I did it...</i>

02:24:21.265 --> 02:24:22.562
<i>...to save him.</i>

02:24:22.767 --> 02:24:26.168
<i>I would have gladly gone</i>
<i>to the electric chair in his place.</i>

02:24:42.553 --> 02:24:44.111
What did he say?

02:24:51.429 --> 02:24:54.728
-I'm so sorry.
-There's nothing to be sorry about.

02:24:55.399 --> 02:24:58.061
I just got a lot of work to do,
that's all.

02:25:02.173 --> 02:25:03.538
How can you work?

02:25:03.741 --> 02:25:05.971
Because we have to teach.

02:25:06.477 --> 02:25:10.140
We gotta teach the people.
We gotta teach on Solomon, Moses...

02:25:10.481 --> 02:25:13.416
...David.
Solomon had 700 wives.

02:25:13.618 --> 02:25:17.019
A man's good deeds,
they far outweigh any of his....

02:25:18.389 --> 02:25:20.414
My father used to say that...

02:25:21.158 --> 02:25:23.888
...you can't make a rooster stop
crowing after sunrise.

02:25:24.095 --> 02:25:25.756
Well, the sun is up.

02:25:48.753 --> 02:25:53.486
So what do I say about this
so-called national day of mourning?

02:25:53.858 --> 02:25:57.350
I say the white man's acts of violence
should be condemned...

02:25:57.562 --> 02:25:59.496
...by our beliefs and by his own.

02:25:59.697 --> 02:26:02.495
The IKoran teaches us that
those who work evil...

02:26:02.967 --> 02:26:07.427
...will be condemned, punished
or judged according to their works.

02:26:07.638 --> 02:26:10.835
<i>The Holy Bible teaches us that</i>
<i>you reap what you sow.</i>

02:26:11.042 --> 02:26:12.509
<i>This is divine justice.</i>

02:26:12.710 --> 02:26:16.544
In the Americas' soil, the white man
has planted seeds of hatred...

02:26:16.747 --> 02:26:18.647
...the seeds of violence.

02:26:18.849 --> 02:26:21.443
He's allowed those weeds to choke...

02:26:21.652 --> 02:26:25.213
...the lives of millions of black men
and women for 400 years...

02:26:25.423 --> 02:26:28.722
...and the lives of Indians in these
Americas for 500 years.

02:26:28.926 --> 02:26:31.019
And now those same weeds...

02:26:31.228 --> 02:26:34.163
...have choked his own chief gardener.

02:26:34.365 --> 02:26:37.596
You ask me what I say.
I only say what the Bible says.

02:26:37.868 --> 02:26:40.132
I say what the IKoran says.

02:26:40.871 --> 02:26:42.566
I say it's justice.

02:26:47.411 --> 02:26:52.348
Don't you even feel a bit remorseful
or saddened by IKennedy's assassination?

02:26:52.883 --> 02:26:56.182
I don't think anyone would deny that
when you send chickens...

02:26:56.387 --> 02:26:58.184
<i>...out from the barnyard...</i>

02:26:58.389 --> 02:27:01.916
<i>...those chickens will return to</i>
<i>your barnyard, not your neighbor's.</i>

02:27:02.126 --> 02:27:05.459
It's an example of the devil's
chickens coming home to roost.

02:27:05.663 --> 02:27:08.689
The violence that he's
perpetrated here and abroad...

02:27:08.899 --> 02:27:12.835
...four children in Birmingham,
or Medgar Evers, or in Africa...

02:27:13.037 --> 02:27:15.528
...this same violence has claimed
one of their own.

02:27:15.740 --> 02:27:19.642
Being a farm boy, chickens coming home
to roost never made me sad.

02:27:19.844 --> 02:27:21.869
In fact, it's only made me glad.

02:27:31.122 --> 02:27:32.419
Did you...

02:27:33.424 --> 02:27:35.915
...read the paper today?

02:27:38.696 --> 02:27:40.357
Yes, sir. I did.

02:27:43.634 --> 02:27:48.571
That was a bad statement you made.

02:27:50.708 --> 02:27:54.337
You knew from my instructions...

02:27:54.612 --> 02:27:59.549
...no minister was to make
any statements against this man.

02:27:59.750 --> 02:28:02.275
The country loved this man.

02:28:02.620 --> 02:28:04.451
You have made it...

02:28:04.889 --> 02:28:06.049
...hard...

02:28:06.891 --> 02:28:08.552
...for Muslims...

02:28:08.926 --> 02:28:10.791
...in general.

02:28:13.330 --> 02:28:14.422
Yes, sir.

02:28:14.632 --> 02:28:19.433
We must disassociate ourselves...

02:28:19.637 --> 02:28:21.935
...from your terrible blunder.

02:28:24.475 --> 02:28:26.466
I must silence you.

02:28:27.078 --> 02:28:28.978
For 90 days...

02:28:32.149 --> 02:28:36.245
...you must not make any statements
to the press...

02:28:36.987 --> 02:28:41.321
...nor are you to speak
at any temples.

02:28:42.660 --> 02:28:43.820
Yes, sir.

02:28:45.429 --> 02:28:48.330
Yes, sir.
I submit 100 percent.

02:29:46.791 --> 02:29:47.883
Leave us alone.

02:29:48.959 --> 02:29:51.189
Leave us alone.
Stop calling here.

02:29:51.395 --> 02:29:54.831
Who's putting you up to this?
We have children here!

02:29:55.132 --> 02:29:56.565
Stop it!

02:30:09.346 --> 02:30:10.677
It's all right.

02:30:11.182 --> 02:30:12.843
They keep calling!

02:30:14.018 --> 02:30:15.849
They keep calling!

02:30:18.422 --> 02:30:19.719
Just...

02:30:21.425 --> 02:30:23.484
...take the babies and put them to bed.

02:30:24.195 --> 02:30:26.527
Come on, babies.
Let's go to bed now.

02:30:27.031 --> 02:30:28.692
-Bedtime.
-Come on.

02:30:29.266 --> 02:30:30.255
Let's go.

02:30:32.002 --> 02:30:35.597
-Good night, Mommy.
-Good night, Daddy.

02:30:50.855 --> 02:30:53.551
Brother Minister,
I have to level with you.

02:30:54.391 --> 02:30:56.382
They gave me a mission...

02:30:56.794 --> 02:30:58.193
...but I couldn't do it.

02:30:59.263 --> 02:31:01.823
-I love you all.
-What kind of mission?

02:31:04.635 --> 02:31:06.603
To wire your car...

02:31:06.804 --> 02:31:09.136
...so it would explode...

02:31:09.573 --> 02:31:11.837
...when you turned the ignition.

02:31:13.143 --> 02:31:17.136
The ministers say you're spreading
untruths about Mr. Muhammad.

02:31:17.581 --> 02:31:20.448
They say that
you're the greatest hypocrite...

02:31:20.651 --> 02:31:22.141
...a Judas...

02:31:22.553 --> 02:31:24.487
...a Benedict Arnold.

02:31:25.890 --> 02:31:29.485
The ministers say that
your tongue should be cut out...

02:31:29.994 --> 02:31:33.225
...and delivered
to Mr. Muhammad's doorstep.

02:31:33.964 --> 02:31:35.693
And what do you say?

02:31:35.900 --> 02:31:37.629
I'm with you, Brother Minister.

02:31:37.835 --> 02:31:39.302
You'll be marked for death.

02:31:39.937 --> 02:31:41.097
Yes, sir.

02:31:42.172 --> 02:31:43.196
Let me die then.

02:31:56.687 --> 02:31:58.882
I can't come between you
and your father.

02:31:59.356 --> 02:32:01.620
-You're my father.
-Go on home.

02:32:03.694 --> 02:32:05.855
Don't come back.
That's an order.

02:32:13.470 --> 02:32:15.062
Yes, sir.

02:32:27.451 --> 02:32:31.387
Because 1964 threatens to be an
explosive year on the racial front...

02:32:31.588 --> 02:32:36.218
...I have called this press conference
to clarify my position.

02:32:36.527 --> 02:32:40.463
Internal differences have forced me
out of the Nation of Islam.

02:32:40.664 --> 02:32:44.691
In the past, I thought and spoke
the words of Elijah Muhammad.

02:32:44.902 --> 02:32:46.802
Everything I said,
I started with:

02:32:47.004 --> 02:32:50.303
"The Honorable Elijah Muhammad
teaches us" thus-and-so.

02:32:50.574 --> 02:32:52.201
That day is over.

02:32:52.409 --> 02:32:56.106
From now on I speak my own words,
and I think my own thoughts.

02:32:56.313 --> 02:32:59.043
<i>Now that I have</i>
<i>more independence of action...</i>

02:32:59.249 --> 02:33:02.650
<i>...I'll use a more flexible approach</i>
<i>in working with others...</i>

02:33:02.853 --> 02:33:04.480
<i>...to solve this problem.</i>

02:33:04.688 --> 02:33:06.986
I'm not out to fight
other Negro leaders.

02:33:07.191 --> 02:33:10.649
L"ve forgotten every bad thing
other leaders said about me...

02:33:10.861 --> 02:33:14.661
...and I pray they'll forget the many
bad things I said about them.

02:33:14.865 --> 02:33:18.926
We must work together to find a common
solution to a common problem.

02:33:19.470 --> 02:33:22.371
<i>I will organize</i>
<i>and lead a new mosque in New York:</i>

02:33:22.573 --> 02:33:24.268
<i>Muslim Mosque, Incorporated.</i>

02:33:24.708 --> 02:33:28.200
<i>This gives us the religious base</i>
<i>and the spiritual force...</i>

02:33:28.412 --> 02:33:31.040
<i>...necessary to rid our people</i>
<i>of the vices...</i>

02:33:31.281 --> 02:33:33.613
<i>...that destroy</i>
<i>our community's moral fiber.</i>

02:33:33.817 --> 02:33:36.183
Our politics
will be Black Nationalism...

02:33:36.387 --> 02:33:39.447
...meaning, we want to control
our community's politics.

02:33:39.656 --> 02:33:42.090
The Muslim Mosque, Inc.
Will remain open...

02:33:42.292 --> 02:33:45.557
...for ideas and financial aid
from all quarters.

02:33:46.130 --> 02:33:49.065
Whites can help us,
but they can't join us.

02:33:49.299 --> 02:33:52.757
There can't be black-white unity
until there's first black unity.

02:33:53.037 --> 02:33:54.664
We can't unite with others...

02:33:54.872 --> 02:33:57.773
...until we've first learned
to unite amongst ourselves.

02:33:57.975 --> 02:34:00.102
We can't be acceptable to others...

02:34:00.310 --> 02:34:03.040
...until we have first
proven acceptable to ourselves.

02:34:03.247 --> 02:34:06.739
<i>In my desire to fully understand</i>
<i>the religion of Islam...</i>

02:34:06.950 --> 02:34:11.046
<i>...as practiced by 750 million</i>
<i>Muslims around the world...</i>

02:34:11.255 --> 02:34:15.658
<i>...I intend to make a pilgrimage,</i>
<i>or holy journey, to Mecca.</i>

02:34:15.859 --> 02:34:18.623
<i>This pilgrimage is</i>
<i>a religious requirement...</i>

02:34:18.829 --> 02:34:21.389
<i>...or duty,</i>
<i>of every Muslim that is able...</i>

02:34:21.598 --> 02:34:25.364
<i>...to make the pilgrimage</i>
<i>at least once in his lifetime.</i>

02:34:39.316 --> 02:34:40.908
I'm Egyptian. And you?

02:34:41.218 --> 02:34:42.310
American.

02:34:42.519 --> 02:34:43.577
What's your name?

02:34:43.787 --> 02:34:46.085
Malcolm.

02:35:00.404 --> 02:35:02.531
-How much?
-Twenty Egyptian pounds.

02:35:03.307 --> 02:35:04.535
For one?

02:35:04.741 --> 02:35:07.107
-Special price for you.
-Special for me!

02:35:07.311 --> 02:35:10.712
Okay, thank you.
Where can I get a better price?

02:35:16.186 --> 02:35:18.086
-What's your name?
-Mohammed.

02:35:18.288 --> 02:35:19.846
Mohammed, I'm Malcolm.

02:35:20.991 --> 02:35:23.482
-Malcolm X. And you?
-Gamaal.

02:35:23.727 --> 02:35:27.686
All right, Gamaal. I'm from Harlem.
From the United States.

02:35:29.500 --> 02:35:32.469
-Hareem?
-No, not Hareem. Harlem.

02:35:32.669 --> 02:35:34.534
Can you show me around?

02:35:34.738 --> 02:35:37.229
-Hash?
-No. No hashish.

02:35:39.243 --> 02:35:40.767
You know, the pyramids.

02:35:41.678 --> 02:35:44.169
No, pyramids, pyramids, pyramids.

02:35:49.987 --> 02:35:51.352
You're gonna take me?

02:35:52.689 --> 02:35:54.884
Sphinx! Sphinx!

02:37:16.340 --> 02:37:18.069
<i>My darling Betty:</i>

02:37:18.575 --> 02:37:22.568
<i>Everywhere I go, I am welcomed</i>
<i>as a representative of our people.</i>

02:37:22.946 --> 02:37:26.109
<i>Our struggle is known</i>
<i>and respected worldwide.</i>

02:37:26.617 --> 02:37:30.383
<i>Coincidentally, two white men</i>
<i>follow me around wherever I go.</i>

02:37:30.754 --> 02:37:32.688
<i>I wonder who they're working for?</i>

02:37:33.190 --> 02:37:35.658
<i>If I was a betting man,</i>
<i>I'd say the CIA.</i>

02:37:35.859 --> 02:37:37.019
<i>What's your guess?</i>

02:37:38.028 --> 02:37:40.053
<i>Today I arrived in Arabia.</i>

02:37:40.697 --> 02:37:44.599
<i>I have never witnessed</i>
<i>such sincere hospitality...</i>

02:37:44.801 --> 02:37:46.894
...and true brotherhood...

02:37:47.104 --> 02:37:48.731
<i>...as practiced here...</i>

02:37:48.939 --> 02:37:52.204
<i>...in the ancient</i>
<i>home of Abraham, Mohammed...</i>

02:37:52.743 --> 02:37:55.940
<i>...and the great prophets</i>
<i>of the Scriptures. "</i>

02:38:02.219 --> 02:38:04.779
<i>Today, with thousands of others...</i>

02:38:04.988 --> 02:38:08.549
<i>...I proclaimed God's greatness</i>
<i>in the sacred city of Mecca.</i>

02:38:09.626 --> 02:38:13.062
<i>In the</i> ihram <i>garb, I made</i>
<i>my seven circuits around the Kaaba.</i>

02:38:13.664 --> 02:38:15.962
<i>I drank from the well of Zem Zem.</i>

02:38:16.400 --> 02:38:19.164
<i>I prayed to Allah from Mount Arafat.</i>

02:38:19.469 --> 02:38:23.371
<i>It was the only time in my life that</i>
<i>I stood before the Creator...</i>

02:38:23.573 --> 02:38:26.064
<i>...and felt</i>
<i>like a complete human being.</i>

02:38:46.263 --> 02:38:48.823
<i>Now, you may be shocked</i>
<i>by these words...</i>

02:38:49.032 --> 02:38:52.900
<i>...but I've eaten from the same plate,</i>
<i>drunk from the same glass...</i>

02:38:53.103 --> 02:38:57.096
<i>...and prayed to the same God</i>
<i>with Muslims whose eyes were blue...</i>

02:38:57.307 --> 02:39:01.573
<i>...whose hair was blond, and whose</i>
<i>skin was the whitest of white.</i>

02:39:01.778 --> 02:39:03.507
<i>And we were all brothers...</i>

02:39:03.714 --> 02:39:04.738
<i>...truly.</i>

02:39:04.948 --> 02:39:09.885
<i>People of all colors and races</i>
<i>believing in one God, in one humanity.</i>

02:39:24.201 --> 02:39:26.431
<i>Each hour in this sacred land</i>
<i>gives me...</i>

02:39:26.636 --> 02:39:30.231
<i>...greater spiritual insight into</i>
<i>what is happening in America.</i>

02:39:30.640 --> 02:39:34.940
<i>The American Negro can never</i>
<i>be blamed for his racial animosities.</i>

02:39:35.145 --> 02:39:39.104
<i>He's only reacting to 400 years of</i>
<i>oppression and discrimination.</i>

02:39:39.316 --> 02:39:42.774
<i>But as racism leads America</i>
<i>up the suicidal path...</i>

02:39:42.986 --> 02:39:46.615
<i>...I believe the younger generation</i>
<i>will see the writing on the wall...</i>

02:39:46.823 --> 02:39:50.224
<i>...and many will want to turn to</i>
<i>the spiritual path of truth...</i>

02:39:50.427 --> 02:39:53.157
<i>...the only way left to ward off</i>
<i>the disaster...</i>

02:39:53.363 --> 02:39:55.331
<i>...that racism must surely lead to.</i>

02:39:56.266 --> 02:40:00.396
<i>Once before, in prison,</i>
<i>the truth came and blinded me.</i>

02:40:01.505 --> 02:40:03.200
<i>Well, it has happened again.</i>

02:40:04.241 --> 02:40:07.768
<i>In the past, I've made sweeping</i>
<i>indictments of all white people.</i>

02:40:08.011 --> 02:40:10.639
<i>And these generalizations</i>
<i>have caused injuries...</i>

02:40:10.847 --> 02:40:13.338
<i>...to some whites</i>
<i>who didn't deserve them.</i>

02:40:14.451 --> 02:40:18.444
"Because of the spiritual rebirth
which I was blessed to undergo...

02:40:18.655 --> 02:40:20.816
...as a result of my pilgrimage...

02:40:21.024 --> 02:40:23.117
...to the holy city of Mecca...

02:40:24.895 --> 02:40:28.661
...I no longer subscribe
to sweeping indictments of one race.

02:40:28.932 --> 02:40:30.365
<i>I intend...</i>

02:40:31.301 --> 02:40:33.496
<i>...to be very careful not to....</i>

02:40:33.703 --> 02:40:37.503
--<i>careful not to sentence anyone</i>
<i>who has not been proven guilty.</i>

02:40:38.141 --> 02:40:40.166
<i>I am not a racist...</i>

02:40:40.377 --> 02:40:43.676
<i>...and I do not subscribe to any</i>
<i>of the tenets of racism.</i>

02:40:43.880 --> 02:40:45.780
<i>In all honesty and sincerity...</i>

02:40:45.982 --> 02:40:50.078
<i>...it can be stated that I wish</i>
<i>nothing but freedom, justice...</i>

02:40:50.287 --> 02:40:51.948
<i>...and equality...</i>

02:40:52.589 --> 02:40:57.322
<i>...life, liberty and the pursuit</i>
<i>of happiness for all people.</i>

02:40:57.727 --> 02:41:00.958
<i>My first concern is with the group</i>
<i>to which I belong...</i>

02:41:01.164 --> 02:41:05.294
<i>...for we, more than others, are</i>
<i>deprived of our inalienable rights.</i>

02:41:05.502 --> 02:41:07.493
<i>But the true practice of Islam...</i>

02:41:07.704 --> 02:41:09.695
<i>...can remove the cancer of racism...</i>

02:41:09.906 --> 02:41:13.535
<i>...from the hearts and the souls</i>
<i>of all Americans.</i>

02:41:13.743 --> 02:41:16.041
<i>If I can die</i>
<i>having brought any light...</i>

02:41:16.246 --> 02:41:21.183
<i>...having exposed any truth that</i>
<i>will help destroy this disease...</i>

02:41:21.918 --> 02:41:25.854
<i>...then all the credit is due to Allah,</i>
<i>the Lord of all the worlds.</i>

02:41:26.323 --> 02:41:28.757
<i>And only the mistakes have been mine.</i>

02:41:30.360 --> 02:41:32.692
<i>Please give all my love</i>
<i>to the children.</i>

02:41:33.196 --> 02:41:34.754
<i>I love you dearly.</i>

02:41:35.699 --> 02:41:38.930
<i>Sincerely,</i>
<i>El-Hajj Malik El-Shabazz...</i>

02:41:39.269 --> 02:41:40.930
<i>...Malcolm X.</i>

02:42:28.685 --> 02:42:29.811
<i>Let's begin.</i>

02:42:30.020 --> 02:42:34.389
<i>You said on your trip you sensed</i>
<i>a feeling of great brotherhood.</i>

02:42:34.591 --> 02:42:38.823
<i>Yes, when I was in Mecca</i>
<i>making the pilgrimage...</i>

02:42:39.729 --> 02:42:43.961
<i>...the brotherhood that existed there</i>
<i>among all people, all races...</i>

02:42:44.167 --> 02:42:48.194
<i>...all levels of people who</i>
<i>had accepted the religion of Islam...</i>

02:42:49.172 --> 02:42:53.768
<i>...what it had done</i>
<i>for those people, despite...</i>

02:42:53.977 --> 02:42:55.945
<i>...their complexion differences....</i>

02:42:56.146 --> 02:42:59.377
<i>Perhaps if people</i>
<i>here in America would try...</i>

02:42:59.583 --> 02:43:03.178
...and practice and study the religion
of Islam, it might help...

02:43:03.386 --> 02:43:07.220
...to erase the plague of racism here.

02:43:07.691 --> 02:43:10.922
I think Muslims over there
look at themselves as...

02:43:11.127 --> 02:43:16.064
...human beings, as part of
the same human family.

02:43:16.533 --> 02:43:18.933
Today my friends are black...

02:43:19.235 --> 02:43:21.635
...red, yellow, brown and white.

02:43:21.838 --> 02:43:26.741
Are you prepared to ask the UN
to bring charges against the U.S...

02:43:26.943 --> 02:43:28.570
...for its treatment of Negroes?

02:43:28.778 --> 02:43:30.678
Oh, yes. Oh, yes.

02:43:32.616 --> 02:43:35.107
The audience will have to be quiet.

02:43:35.919 --> 02:43:37.614
<i>Please, please.</i>

02:43:38.555 --> 02:43:41.217
<i>Yes, as I stated earlier...</i>

02:43:42.225 --> 02:43:45.319
<i>...those nations,</i>
<i>African, Latin, Asian nations...</i>

02:43:45.528 --> 02:43:48.520
<i>...are hypocritical</i>
<i>when they stand up in the UN...</i>

02:43:48.732 --> 02:43:52.133
<i>...and denounce the racism practiced</i>
<i>in South Africa, but...</i>

02:43:52.335 --> 02:43:54.963
...say absolutely nothing about...

02:43:55.238 --> 02:43:58.366
...the practice of racism here
in American society.

02:43:58.575 --> 02:44:01.237
Now, I wouldn't be a man
if I didn't do so.

02:44:01.444 --> 02:44:06.381
Will you work now with leaders
of other civil rights organizations?

02:44:06.583 --> 02:44:10.644
Yes, we're prepared to work with
any groups, leaders, organizations...

02:44:10.854 --> 02:44:14.415
...as long as they're
genuinely interested in results.

02:44:14.624 --> 02:44:15.556
Positive results.

02:44:15.759 --> 02:44:18.489
Does your new beard have any
religious significance?

02:44:19.763 --> 02:44:21.856
No, not particularly, but...

02:44:22.198 --> 02:44:25.690
...I think that as black people
in America strive...

02:44:25.902 --> 02:44:29.463
...to throw off the shackles
of mental colonialism...

02:44:29.673 --> 02:44:31.698
...they'll also reflect
their desire...

02:44:31.908 --> 02:44:34.900
...to throw off the shackles of
cultural colonialism.

02:44:35.111 --> 02:44:38.911
I believe that a mental and cultural
migration back to Africa...

02:44:39.115 --> 02:44:41.140
...not necessarily a physical one...

02:44:41.351 --> 02:44:44.946
...but a mental and cultural
migration back to Africa...

02:44:45.155 --> 02:44:49.285
...which means we reaffirm our bond
with our brothers over there...

02:44:49.592 --> 02:44:53.756
...would help to strengthen
black people in America.

02:44:53.963 --> 02:44:57.262
Not only spiritually,
but it would give us the incentive...

02:44:57.467 --> 02:45:00.664
...to solve some of our problems
here at home.

02:45:00.870 --> 02:45:03.464
One of your
more controversial remarks...

02:45:03.673 --> 02:45:06.801
...called for black people to get
rifles and form clubs.

02:45:07.010 --> 02:45:08.705
Do you still favor that idea?

02:45:08.878 --> 02:45:10.903
Why is that controversial?

02:45:11.114 --> 02:45:14.015
If white people find themselves
the victims of...

02:45:14.217 --> 02:45:18.745
...the violence black people found
themselves victims of in America...

02:45:18.955 --> 02:45:22.686
...and if the government was unable
or unwilling to do anything...

02:45:22.892 --> 02:45:26.020
...it'd be intelligence on their part
to defend themselves.

02:45:26.229 --> 02:45:27.753
What about the guns?

02:45:29.632 --> 02:45:33.432
When you tell your people to stop
being violent against my people...

02:45:33.636 --> 02:45:35.695
...l'll tell them
to put away their guns.

02:45:35.905 --> 02:45:37.429
So you're still an extremist.

02:45:37.741 --> 02:45:39.606
<i>Get your hand out of my pocket!</i>

02:45:46.616 --> 02:45:47.446
Next question.

02:46:07.704 --> 02:46:11.401
<i>Malcolm, you one dead, red nigger.</i>

02:46:11.975 --> 02:46:15.911
<i>Your days on this earth are</i>
<i>numbered, brother.</i>

02:46:28.291 --> 02:46:29.417
Come to bed.

02:46:30.026 --> 02:46:31.789
Get some rest.

02:46:37.300 --> 02:46:38.790
I'm sorry, Betty.

02:46:40.370 --> 02:46:41.428
Sorry for what?

02:46:41.638 --> 02:46:45.301
I haven't been the best husband
or the best father.

02:46:45.508 --> 02:46:48.102
A family shouldn't be separated
like ours has been.

02:46:48.311 --> 02:46:51.974
I promise I'll never make a long trip
without you and the children.

02:46:55.652 --> 02:46:57.210
I miss you and the girls.

02:47:03.326 --> 02:47:05.317
We will be together,
I promise you that.

02:47:06.663 --> 02:47:07.721
Dear heart....

02:47:10.066 --> 02:47:11.556
I love you.

02:47:16.272 --> 02:47:17.864
Thank you.

02:47:25.381 --> 02:47:27.178
Now get some sleep.

02:47:32.088 --> 02:47:35.353
We had the best organization
the black man has ever seen.

02:47:36.759 --> 02:47:38.056
Niggers ruined it.

02:48:09.292 --> 02:48:10.589
Wake up!

02:48:14.731 --> 02:48:16.130
Come on! Let's get up!

02:48:16.332 --> 02:48:18.698
Girls, come on! Come on!
Out! Out!

02:48:19.068 --> 02:48:20.558
Outside! Out!

02:48:22.705 --> 02:48:25.105
Go, go! Run, run!

02:48:25.308 --> 02:48:27.538
Go across the street!

02:48:27.744 --> 02:48:30.679
-Somebody call the fire department!
-Help! Help!

02:48:32.048 --> 02:48:34.073
Call the fire department, please!

02:48:34.284 --> 02:48:36.309
Somebody call the fire department!

02:48:36.519 --> 02:48:37.781
I'm a man!

02:48:37.987 --> 02:48:39.215
Evidently...

02:48:40.657 --> 02:48:44.559
...some type of bomb was thrown against
the back of the house.

02:48:44.761 --> 02:48:47.787
One was thrown on the side
of the house, from what I see.

02:48:50.934 --> 02:48:53.903
It bounced up against the window
and woke my daughter.

02:48:54.103 --> 02:48:57.072
Had it gone inside,
my 2-year-old, my 4-year-old...

02:48:57.273 --> 02:48:59.002
...and my 6-year-old daughter....

02:48:59.676 --> 02:49:02.076
Had that happened,
I'd have taken my rifle...

02:49:02.278 --> 02:49:03.905
...and gone after anyone in sight.

02:49:04.113 --> 02:49:06.911
Was this a warning
or an attempt on your life?

02:49:07.116 --> 02:49:09.516
What, does it look like
a warning to you?

02:49:09.719 --> 02:49:11.448
This was a definite attempt...

02:49:11.788 --> 02:49:15.417
...by the Nation of Islam, upon
the strict orders of Elijah Muhammad.

02:49:15.625 --> 02:49:18.719
-Muslim headquarters say--
-I don't care what they say.

02:49:18.928 --> 02:49:20.293
I see what they're doing.

02:49:20.496 --> 02:49:24.159
Minister Baines, can you tell us
who bombed the house?

02:49:24.434 --> 02:49:28.302
We feel it's a publicity stunt
on the part of Malcolm X.

02:49:28.538 --> 02:49:30.130
We hope it's not so that...

02:49:30.340 --> 02:49:33.434
...if he can't keep the house,
we won't get it either.

02:49:33.643 --> 02:49:35.133
That's enough. Excuse me.

02:49:41.718 --> 02:49:42.946
I'm all right. I'm all right.

02:49:43.152 --> 02:49:44.949
-Betty and the kids?
-They're fine.

02:49:45.154 --> 02:49:47.349
Let's post some
men in front of the house.

02:49:47.557 --> 02:49:50.458
-Did you see anybody?
-No, but I know who it is.

02:49:50.660 --> 02:49:53.026
-You know I know who did it.
-Give us the command.

02:49:53.229 --> 02:49:56.995
Don't worry about the command.
Two men on post, two in front!

02:50:31.401 --> 02:50:32.493
Spark it.

02:50:42.612 --> 02:50:44.603
As-Salaam-Alaikum, my brothers.

02:50:47.383 --> 02:50:50.113
-Here's your key. Enjoy your stay.
-Thank you.

02:50:53.890 --> 02:50:55.551
O.A.A.U.

02:50:56.926 --> 02:50:58.985
Brother Earl, it's Malcolm.

02:51:02.298 --> 02:51:05.859
Where are you? We've been calling
all over the city.

02:51:06.135 --> 02:51:07.466
Hold the phone.

02:51:16.012 --> 02:51:17.912
<i>I'm downtown.</i>

02:51:18.247 --> 02:51:21.546
<i>I'm in a hotel trying</i>
<i>to get some work done for tomorrow.</i>

02:51:21.751 --> 02:51:24.584
-Let me bring some brothers there.
-<i>That's all right.</i>

02:51:24.887 --> 02:51:26.980
<i>I wish you'd listen to us.</i>

02:51:27.190 --> 02:51:30.387
We must frisk people
at the Audubon Ballroom meeting.

02:51:30.593 --> 02:51:33.118
No, no! I don't want....

02:51:33.429 --> 02:51:35.420
I don't want anybody frisked.

02:51:37.600 --> 02:51:39.625
We have to change our way of thinking.

02:51:39.836 --> 02:51:41.963
We have to make people
feel comfortable.

02:51:42.171 --> 02:51:45.732
<i>If I can't be safe around my own kind,</i>
<i>who can I be safe around?</i>

02:51:45.942 --> 02:51:47.773
<i>I trust Allah will protect me.</i>

02:51:47.977 --> 02:51:52.209
Believing in Allah is one thing,
but I also believe in being armed.

02:51:55.451 --> 02:51:59.114
We don't want black people
killing each other, all right?

02:52:01.557 --> 02:52:02.581
All right?

02:52:02.792 --> 02:52:04.521
We'll protect you, Malcolm.

02:52:05.294 --> 02:52:06.522
As-Salaam-Alaikum.

02:52:06.729 --> 02:52:09.357
<i>No, peace be unto you, Earl.</i>

02:52:47.069 --> 02:52:49.401
Do you have a Malcolm X registered?

02:53:46.996 --> 02:53:50.432
<i>Your red nigger is dead</i>
<i>and so are your bastard children!</i>

02:54:15.725 --> 02:54:17.249
<i>Wake up, brother.</i>

02:54:17.827 --> 02:54:19.692
As-Salaam-Alaikum.

02:54:27.937 --> 02:54:31.429
You hear me and hear me well.
You come anywhere near my family...

02:54:31.674 --> 02:54:33.608
-...and I will kill you.
-<i>Betty?</i>

02:54:33.809 --> 02:54:35.106
Do you hear?

02:54:36.279 --> 02:54:37.803
Betty, it's me, Malcolm.

02:54:44.553 --> 02:54:46.248
They keep calling.

02:54:46.455 --> 02:54:49.754
They keep threatening. I go crazy
every time a phone rings.

02:54:49.959 --> 02:54:53.156
Just don't answer the phone.
Everything'll be all right.

02:54:53.362 --> 02:54:55.853
-<i>When will it stop?</i>
-<i>Don't answer the phone.</i>

02:54:57.033 --> 02:54:59.126
<i>Are the brothers there on post?</i>

02:55:00.136 --> 02:55:01.433
They're outside.

02:55:01.637 --> 02:55:04.435
<i>Let them answer the phone.</i>
<i>Don't touch the phone.</i>

02:55:04.640 --> 02:55:05.834
Beloved, where are you?

02:55:06.042 --> 02:55:07.737
I'm in a hotel.

02:55:09.145 --> 02:55:09.975
In a hotel.

02:55:10.379 --> 02:55:11.812
<i>The girls asleep?</i>

02:55:13.215 --> 02:55:16.309
I just put them down to bed.

02:55:17.219 --> 02:55:19.380
<i>Can we come to the meeting tomorrow?</i>

02:55:21.691 --> 02:55:23.318
No, I don't think so.

02:55:24.327 --> 02:55:27.160
<i>The girls and I want to see you.</i>
<i>We miss you.</i>

02:55:28.064 --> 02:55:30.055
Betty, it's too dangerous.

02:55:30.833 --> 02:55:32.960
<i>It's been dangerous.</i>

02:55:36.138 --> 02:55:39.198
Listen, I haven't told
this to anybody...

02:55:41.911 --> 02:55:43.708
...but I've been thinking...

02:55:43.913 --> 02:55:47.246
...about what's been happening to me
lately, to us lately...

02:55:48.084 --> 02:55:51.485
...and I'm gonna stop saying
The Nation of Islam's behind this.

02:55:51.687 --> 02:55:55.088
I know what they can and can't do.
I trained them.

02:55:56.926 --> 02:56:00.020
Some of the things that have
been happening lately....

02:56:02.098 --> 02:56:05.329
I'm gonna stop staying it's just
The Nation of Islam.

02:56:05.534 --> 02:56:07.593
They're not working alone.

02:56:08.204 --> 02:56:10.069
They're getting a lot of help.

02:56:10.272 --> 02:56:12.035
<i>Are you sure?</i>

02:56:12.942 --> 02:56:14.375
<i>I miss you, Betty.</i>

02:56:18.013 --> 02:56:20.413
<i>You're with us</i>
<i>even when you're away.</i>

02:56:20.616 --> 02:56:23.949
<i>Now listen, you come on down to</i>
<i>the Audubon tomorrow.</i>

02:56:25.054 --> 02:56:28.683
<i>We'll be all right.</i>
<i>We're not gonna let this get us down.</i>

02:56:28.891 --> 02:56:31.018
<i>You come on down.</i>
<i>Bring the girls too.</i>

02:56:31.227 --> 02:56:33.718
<i>The girls and I miss you so much.</i>

02:56:34.063 --> 02:56:35.189
<i>I'll see you tomorrow.</i>

02:56:35.398 --> 02:56:37.491
Compared to IKing, this guy's a monk.

02:56:37.700 --> 02:56:39.725
<i>Good night.</i>
<i>Sleep well. I love you.</i>

02:56:39.935 --> 02:56:40.765
<i>Good night.</i>

02:56:53.783 --> 02:56:56.445
Sweetheart, Attallah, sit back.

02:56:56.652 --> 02:56:59.849
Sit up.
Sit up straight.

02:57:25.181 --> 02:57:27.775
Mama, I want the doll!

02:58:14.330 --> 02:58:15.297
Sister?

02:58:19.068 --> 02:58:22.003
-What do you say to the nice man?
-Thank you.

02:58:22.204 --> 02:58:24.331
You're very welcome,
my beautiful sister.

02:58:25.474 --> 02:58:26.532
Bye-bye.

02:58:42.925 --> 02:58:45.223
The minister hasn't arrived yet.

02:58:45.528 --> 02:58:48.053
Don't worry.
He'll be here like clockwork.

02:59:21.163 --> 02:59:22.255
Son?

02:59:22.464 --> 02:59:23.556
Son?

02:59:24.733 --> 02:59:26.200
Are you all right?

02:59:26.435 --> 02:59:27.459
Are you okay?

02:59:30.839 --> 02:59:33.205
Good.
I recognize you.

02:59:33.409 --> 02:59:35.934
Don't you pay them folks
no never mind.

02:59:36.145 --> 02:59:38.773
You just keep right on doing
what you doing.

02:59:40.849 --> 02:59:41.975
Yes, ma'am.

02:59:42.651 --> 02:59:44.915
-I'll pray for you, son.
-Well, thank you.

02:59:45.321 --> 02:59:47.186
Jesus will protect you.

03:00:01.637 --> 03:00:03.400
Is the charter ready?

03:00:03.606 --> 03:00:05.403
No, Brother Minister.

03:00:07.009 --> 03:00:08.442
No? Why not?

03:00:10.846 --> 03:00:12.746
You had enough time, didn't you?

03:00:12.948 --> 03:00:15.246
I apologize.
We'll have it next week.

03:00:15.451 --> 03:00:17.749
We don't have next week.
We need it today.

03:00:17.953 --> 03:00:20.319
The people want to hear
the charter today.

03:00:20.522 --> 03:00:22.183
Next week, Minister.

03:00:28.664 --> 03:00:30.029
Is the reverend here?

03:00:30.366 --> 03:00:33.665
The reverend called and said
he wouldn't be able to attend.

03:00:35.137 --> 03:00:38.629
So now we don't have
an opening speaker or a charter....

03:00:39.441 --> 03:00:42.274
Why didn't you say this last night
when I talked to you?

03:00:42.478 --> 03:00:45.345
-I called Sister Betty.
-You didn't have to call her!

03:00:45.547 --> 03:00:47.515
You should've told me!
Why tell her?

03:00:47.716 --> 03:00:49.980
-I assumed that--
-Don't assume anything!

03:01:00.529 --> 03:01:01.689
Go on down front.

03:01:01.997 --> 03:01:04.557
-Sister, you go on with the brother.
-Yes, sir.

03:01:23.218 --> 03:01:24.412
What's wrong?

03:01:28.924 --> 03:01:31.256
It's a time for martyrs now.

03:01:34.963 --> 03:01:36.828
The way I feel...

03:01:38.267 --> 03:01:40.326
...I shouldn't go out there today.

03:01:41.937 --> 03:01:44.428
Fine. Let's cancel it.

03:01:47.443 --> 03:01:49.604
My wife out there?
My children?

03:01:50.012 --> 03:01:52.003
Down front, as always.

03:01:55.017 --> 03:01:57.679
Go out to the pay phone outside.

03:01:59.188 --> 03:02:03.488
Call up the reverend,
see if he can make it down here.

03:02:03.692 --> 03:02:05.489
I gotta be on post.

03:02:05.694 --> 03:02:07.855
I'm supposed to be
guarding you.

03:02:08.063 --> 03:02:13.000
-Besides, that's a duty for secretaries--
-Go out to the pay phone.

03:02:13.535 --> 03:02:15.127
Call up the reverend.

03:02:15.637 --> 03:02:17.468
See if he can make it down here.

03:02:21.944 --> 03:02:23.138
Fine.

03:03:18.500 --> 03:03:19.762
Thank you.

03:03:24.573 --> 03:03:27.406
I apologize for
raising my voice earlier.

03:03:27.609 --> 03:03:29.201
It was very disrespectful.

03:03:29.444 --> 03:03:31.935
Brother Minister, I understand.

03:03:40.889 --> 03:03:42.186
Why styles are changing...

03:03:42.524 --> 03:03:45.322
...minds are changing,
why everything is changing.

03:03:45.994 --> 03:03:50.055
So you and I must consider that
we're living in very changing times.

03:03:50.465 --> 03:03:53.923
And what might be true today
may not be true tomorrow.

03:03:54.837 --> 03:03:57.499
And without any further ado,
I present to you...

03:03:57.973 --> 03:04:00.669
...Brother Minister Malcolm.
And I pray...

03:04:01.143 --> 03:04:04.840
...that you and I will listen.
Listen...

03:04:05.480 --> 03:04:07.971
...hear and understand.

03:04:08.183 --> 03:04:09.013
Thank you.

03:04:16.024 --> 03:04:17.389
Daddy!

03:04:31.673 --> 03:04:33.834
Get your hand out of my pocket!

03:04:35.611 --> 03:04:36.703
Brother....

03:04:36.912 --> 03:04:38.004
Please. Hold it.

03:04:39.681 --> 03:04:41.672
Calm down.
Please, brothers!

03:04:41.884 --> 03:04:42.816
Brothers....

03:05:24.559 --> 03:05:26.652
Get an ambulance!

03:05:26.862 --> 03:05:27.886
Get an ambulance!

03:05:28.163 --> 03:05:29.289
They killed him!

03:05:31.066 --> 03:05:33.057
They killed him!

03:06:52.080 --> 03:06:53.513
Get out of the way!

03:06:58.787 --> 03:06:59.617
Move!

03:07:07.996 --> 03:07:09.361
Stand back!

03:07:09.898 --> 03:07:10.887
Get back!

03:07:12.834 --> 03:07:15.302
Give us a statement, sir!
Please!

03:07:15.504 --> 03:07:18.940
The person you know
as Malcolm X is no more.

03:07:19.274 --> 03:07:21.265
The assassination...

03:07:21.510 --> 03:07:25.105
...of Malcolm X
was an unfortunate tragedy.

03:07:25.514 --> 03:07:28.176
And it reveals
that there are still...

03:07:28.517 --> 03:07:31.611
...numerous people
in our nation who have...

03:07:31.853 --> 03:07:36.517
...degenerated to the point of
expressing dissent through murder...

03:07:36.792 --> 03:07:39.090
...and we haven't learned
to disagree...

03:07:39.294 --> 03:07:41.353
...without being
violently disagreeable.

03:07:42.631 --> 03:07:43.689
<i>Here...</i>

03:07:44.466 --> 03:07:47.128
<i>...at this final hour...</i>

03:07:47.702 --> 03:07:49.966
<i>...in this quiet place...</i>

03:07:50.672 --> 03:07:52.970
<i>...Harlem has come to bid farewell...</i>

03:07:53.175 --> 03:07:55.575
<i>...to one of its brightest hopes...</i>

03:07:56.611 --> 03:07:58.579
<i>...extinguished now...</i>

03:07:59.047 --> 03:08:01.709
<i>...and gone from us forever.</i>

03:08:02.617 --> 03:08:05.643
<i>It is not in the memory</i>
<i>of man that this...</i>

03:08:05.854 --> 03:08:07.412
<i>...beleaguered, unfortunate...</i>

03:08:07.622 --> 03:08:09.749
<i>...but nonetheless proud community...</i>

03:08:10.158 --> 03:08:14.561
<i>...has found a braver,</i>
<i>more gallant young champion...</i>

03:08:14.830 --> 03:08:18.288
<i>...than this Afro-American</i>
<i>who lies before us...</i>

03:08:19.234 --> 03:08:21.225
<i>...unconquered still.</i>

03:08:23.138 --> 03:08:25.504
<i>I say the word again as</i>
<i>he would want me to:</i>

03:08:25.707 --> 03:08:27.072
<i>Afro-American.</i>

03:08:27.309 --> 03:08:30.608
<i>Afro-American Malcolm.</i>

03:08:30.812 --> 03:08:33.542
<i>Malcolm had stopped being "Negro"...</i>

03:08:33.748 --> 03:08:35.079
<i>...years ago.</i>

03:08:35.317 --> 03:08:40.254
<i>It had become too small, too puny,</i>
<i>too weak a word for him.</i>

03:08:40.589 --> 03:08:42.784
<i>Malcolm was bigger than that.</i>

03:08:43.091 --> 03:08:44.388
<i>Malcolm had become...</i>

03:08:44.626 --> 03:08:46.856
<i>...an Afro-American.</i>

03:08:47.129 --> 03:08:49.359
<i>And he wanted so desperately...</i>

03:08:49.898 --> 03:08:52.492
<i>...that we,</i>
<i>that all his people...</i>

03:08:52.701 --> 03:08:55.795
<i>...would become Afro-Americans too.</i>

03:08:59.808 --> 03:09:03.266
<i>There are those who</i>
<i>still consider it their duty...</i>

03:09:03.478 --> 03:09:07.175
<i>...as friends of the Negro people,</i>
<i>to tell us...</i>

03:09:07.716 --> 03:09:09.445
<i>...to revile him.</i>

03:09:09.651 --> 03:09:12.950
<i>To flee, even from</i>
<i>the presence of his memory.</i>

03:09:13.155 --> 03:09:14.679
<i>To save ourselves...</i>

03:09:14.890 --> 03:09:19.452
<i>...by writing him out of</i>
<i>the history of our turbulent times.</i>

03:09:19.828 --> 03:09:21.887
<i>And we will smile.</i>

03:09:22.197 --> 03:09:24.529
<i>They will say that</i>
<i>he is of hate, a fanatic...</i>

03:09:24.733 --> 03:09:27.725
<i>...a racist, who can only bring</i>
<i>evil to the cause...</i>

03:09:27.936 --> 03:09:29.369
<i>...for which you struggle.</i>

03:09:29.571 --> 03:09:32.540
<i>And we will answer and</i>
<i>say unto them:</i>

03:09:32.741 --> 03:09:34.709
<i>"Did you ever talk...</i>

03:09:35.076 --> 03:09:36.737
<i>...to Brother Malcolm?</i>

03:09:37.379 --> 03:09:39.210
<i>Did you ever touch him...</i>

03:09:39.414 --> 03:09:41.541
<i>...or have him smile at you?</i>

03:09:41.750 --> 03:09:44.082
<i>Did you ever really listen to him?"</i>

03:09:46.321 --> 03:09:50.553
<i>"Was he ever associated with violence</i>
<i>or any public disturbance?</i>

03:09:50.759 --> 03:09:53.660
<i>For if you did, you would know him.</i>

03:09:53.862 --> 03:09:55.352
<i>And if you knew him...</i>

03:09:55.597 --> 03:09:59.328
<i>...you would know why</i>
<i>we must honor him. "</i>

03:09:59.534 --> 03:10:03.868
<i>Malcolm was our manhood.</i>
<i>Our living, black manhood.</i>

03:10:04.105 --> 03:10:06.164
<i>This was his meaning</i>
<i>to his people.</i>

03:10:06.441 --> 03:10:11.037
<i>And in honoring him, we honor</i>
<i>the best in ourselves.</i>

03:10:12.414 --> 03:10:15.076
<i>However much we may have</i>
<i>differed with him...</i>

03:10:15.283 --> 03:10:18.343
<i>...or with each other about him</i>
<i>and his value as a man...</i>

03:10:18.553 --> 03:10:20.680
<i>...let his going from us serve...</i>

03:10:20.889 --> 03:10:23.949
<i>...only to bring us together now...</i>

03:10:24.960 --> 03:10:27.622
<i>...consigning these mortal</i>
<i>remains to earth...</i>

03:10:28.129 --> 03:10:30.188
<i>...the common mother of all...</i>

03:10:30.398 --> 03:10:33.731
<i>...secure in the knowledge</i>
<i>that what we place in the ground...</i>

03:10:33.935 --> 03:10:35.266
<i>...is no more now a man...</i>

03:10:35.537 --> 03:10:37.061
<i>...but a seed...</i>

03:10:37.405 --> 03:10:40.374
<i>...which after the winter of</i>
<i>our discontent...</i>

03:10:40.575 --> 03:10:43.442
<i>...will come forth again</i>
<i>to meet us.</i>

03:10:43.645 --> 03:10:45.875
<i>And we shall know him then...</i>

03:10:46.081 --> 03:10:48.948
<i>...for what he was and is:</i>

03:10:49.150 --> 03:10:50.947
<i>A prince.</i>

03:10:51.152 --> 03:10:54.747
<i>Our own black shining prince...</i>

03:10:55.490 --> 03:10:58.653
<i>...who didn't hesitate to die...</i>

03:10:58.994 --> 03:11:00.325
<i>...because...</i>

03:11:00.996 --> 03:11:02.623
<i>...he loved us so.</i>

03:11:03.365 --> 03:11:04.559
<i>And so today...</i>

03:11:04.766 --> 03:11:07.929
...May 19, we celebrate
Malcolm X's birthday...

03:11:08.169 --> 03:11:12.003
...because he was
a great, great Afro-American.

03:11:12.274 --> 03:11:14.936
Malcolm X is you, all of you.

03:11:15.343 --> 03:11:17.402
And you are Malcolm X.

03:11:17.946 --> 03:11:18.970
I'm Malcolm X!

03:11:19.180 --> 03:11:20.238
I'm Malcolm X!

03:11:20.515 --> 03:11:21.413
I'm Malcolm X!

03:11:30.859 --> 03:11:33.350
As Brother Malcolm said:

03:11:36.197 --> 03:11:38.131
"We declare...

03:11:39.467 --> 03:11:41.128
...our right...

03:11:43.271 --> 03:11:44.966
...on this earth...

03:11:46.341 --> 03:11:47.933
...to be a man...

03:11:50.178 --> 03:11:52.339
...to be a human being...

03:11:54.616 --> 03:11:57.016
...to be given the rights...

03:11:57.786 --> 03:11:59.515
...of a human being...

03:12:01.356 --> 03:12:03.187
...to be respected...

03:12:04.359 --> 03:12:06.623
...as a human being...

03:12:07.529 --> 03:12:09.793
...in this society...

03:12:11.032 --> 03:12:12.863
...on this earth...

03:12:14.369 --> 03:12:16.200
...in this day...

03:12:16.805 --> 03:12:19.433
...which we intend to bring...

03:12:19.641 --> 03:12:20.972
...into existence--"

03:12:21.176 --> 03:12:24.009
--by any means necessary!

